Commentary: Starts with a length ball outside off, KL Rahul leaves it through towards the keeper.
On a length angling in, KL Rahul opens the face of the bat and taps it to short covers.

FOUR! Poor delivery angling down leg, KL Rahul just gives it a fine tickle as the ball races away the fine leg fence. Easy pickings! First boundary of the Test match and India and KL Rahul are underway!
Good length angling it into the batter, KL Rahul defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, on middle. KL Rahul defends it solidly.
Good length again shaping it away from the batter, KL Rahul leaves the harmless delivery.
Bowls it outside leg, Shubman Gill leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Another length ball, this one lands on off. Shubman Gill defends it to short covers.
On a length and down leg, Shubman Gill looks to flick it but misses and the ball brushes this thigh pad and rolls towards the keeper.
Bowls it outside leg, Shubman Gill shoulders arms at it.
Similar to the last delivery shaping it away, Shubman Gill leaves it alone towards the keeper again.
Shubman Gill is away. A yorker length and on off, Shubman Gill digs it to mid on and scampers through for a single.
On a length and on off, Shubman Gill defends it to point.
On a length shaping it away from the batter, Shubman Gill lets it go towards the keeper.
Good length angling it into the batter, Shubman Gill fends it to mid on.
Another length ball on off, Shubman Gill defends it but gets an outside edge towards gully. Dot.
Slightly shorter one, Shubman Gill pulls it to backward square leg. The fielder at fine leg runs and collects it. They collect two runs.
Back of a length angling away, Shubman Gill lets it go through to the keeper to end the over.
FOUR! Bowls it fuller and outside off, KL Rahul gets on his knee and guides it through backward point for a boundary!
Back of a length angling away, KL Rahul lets it go through to the keeper.
On a length and on middle, KL Rahul defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball outside off as KL Rahul leaves this one to the keeper.
On a length and shapes it away, this one kept a tad low. KL Rahul looks to defend it but misses. Close!
This one lands outside off as well, KL Rahul looks to block it but misses again.
On a length and just outside off, this one keeps a tad low. Shubman Gill reads it well and makes a tight leave.
FOUR! Good length and just outside off, Shubman Gill hangs back and guides it in the gap through the cover-point region for a boundary!
Fuller and on leg, Shubman Gill defends it to short mid-wicket.
Touch fuller and on off, Shubman Gill defends it to covers.
Slightly shorter one as Shubman Gill defends it back towards Ebadot Hossain.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill stands tall and eases it to the fielder at point.
Slower one on off, KL Rahul punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
FOUR! Another slower one outside off, KL Rahul waits for the ball and cuts it in the gap through point for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, KL Rahul defends it to mid on.
Another fuller one and on middle, KL Rahul defends it to point.
Bowls it on middle again, KL Rahul flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill taps it to covers for one.
On a length and on off, Shubman Gill defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball and outside off, Shubman Gill defends it to short covers.
FOUR! Fine shot. Length and outside off, Shubman Gill rocks back an chops it in the gap through the cover-point region for a boundary!

NO BALL AND FOUR! Back to back boundaries. Slightly shorter one and on off, Shubman Gill pulls it hard and through mid-wicket for another boundary! Oh, its a no ball as well as Ebadot Hossain has overstepped.
Length and on off, Shubman Gill guides it to the fielder at point.
On a length and on leg, Shubman Gill defends it to short mid-wicket.
Good length angling it into the batter as Shubman Gill defends it to covers.
Tossed up, on middle. KL Rahul defends it to mid off.
Fuller again, and on off. KL Rahul defends it to mid off again.
Another fuller ball as this is again blocked towards mid off.
Bowls it outside off, KL Rahul eases it to the fielder at point.
Bowls it on leg, KL Rahul flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Fuller and on off, KL Rahul defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill defends it to mid on.
Good length angling it into the batter, Shubman Gill flicks it to backward square leg for one.
On a length and on leg, KL Rahul fends it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off this time as KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Fuller and outside off shaping it in, KL Rahul looks to defend it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards short fine leg. They collect one. Close!
On a length and on off, Shubman Gill defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, KL Rahul eases it to the fielder at covers.
This one lands on leg, KL Rahul knocks it to mid on for one.
Another fuller one and on off, Shubman Gill eases it to short mid-wicket.
Tosses it up on off, Shubman Gill defends it to short covers.
Bowls it outside off, Shubman Gill moves forward and guides it to deep covers for one more.
Fuller length around off, KL Rahul pushes it to the cover fielder for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul fends it towards the off side with ease.
Angles a length delivery on off as he goes wide of the crease and Rahul makes a solid block again from his crease.
Good effort ball! Bowls it short and around off. Rahul sways away from the line of the ball.
Lands it on a good length and outside off at 138 kph. Rahul sees it carefully and leaves it alone.
Pulls his length back and on off. Rahul gets right behind it and defends it towards the off side.
Nice delivery and it's a maiden! On a good length and outside off. It shapes into Rahul and he lets it go keeping his bat inside the line of the ball.
Tossed up, on off. Gill tries to drive it but gets a thick outside edge that goes off the bounce to point.
Loopy delivery again on off. Gill drives it firmly to long off for a single this time.
Bowls it fuller and on middle at 82 kph. Rahul works it wide of mid on for a single.
Pushes it bit quicker on off at 88 kph. Gill blocks it off the front foot.
Lovely loopy delivery on middle. Gill fends it towards the off side.
Slower through the air and on off. Gill drives but finds the cover fielder.
Goes fuller and on middle at 137 kph. Rahul drives it firmly to mid off.
Back of a length and around off. Rahul steers it towards third man for a single.
Lands it on a length, on off. Gill defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
Serves it full and drifts it on the pads. Rahul flicks it past the square leg fielder for a couple.
Solid block! On a length, on middle. Rahul defends it off the front foot.
On a length and angling into middle at 138 kph. Rahul dabs it towards the off side and looks for a single but is sent back by his partner.
Tossed up nicely on middle at 86 kph. Gill defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shubman Gill departs and Taijul Islam finds the breakthrough! Gill would be extremely disappointed with this, he was looking quite comfortable in the middle but one poor shot has brought his downfall here. Taijul Islam is the man again for Bangladesh, he has really been brilliant in Bangladeshi conditions. This one is slower through the air on middle. Gill tries to do something different and tries to paddle it. However, the ball goes off the top edge behind and left of the keeper. Yasir Ali though is aware of it and runs to his left from slip and takes a fine catch.
Howout: c Yasir Ali b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Bowls it quicker and flatter on off. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Lovely delivery on off. Bit of turn away from the batter and Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Again keeps it on the same line and length and Pujara is solid in his defence.
Slower through the air, on off. Pujara defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side. A wicket-maiden from Taijul Islam! Brilliant over.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahul works it towards the square leg fielder.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Rahul with a solid block onto the turf.
Short of good length, on off at 139 kph. Rahul defends it from his crease.
Back of a length, on middle at 138 kph. Rahul works it to short mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahul rides the bounce and defends it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on off. Rahul drives it to the mid off fielder. Another maiden!
Lovely bowling, just short of full length on middle. Bit of turn away from the batter. Pujara tries to defend it but gets a thick outside edge towards the off side.
A tossed up delivery on middle. Pujara defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side and a single is taken.
Tossed up, on off. Rahul drives it to long off for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle Pujara skips down the track and works it to short mid-wicket.
Bowls it quicker and around off. Pujara takes his front foot forward and defends it.
Good delivery and another very fine over from Taijul Islam! Loopy delivery on off. Pujara skips down the track and defends it back to the bowler. Good drift on this delivery.
Goes fuller and on off. Rahul drives it to mid off.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off. Rahul with a solid block again.
Skiddy delivery, lands it on a length, on off. Rahul defends it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller and on middle at 138 kph. Rahul drives it to mid off. Both the Bangladeshi bowlers are now bowling with lot more penetration and accuracy.
On a good length and around off. Rahul defends it towards deep point for a single.
Goes fuller and on the pads. Pujara flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Pushes it quicker on off. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and around off. Pujara pushes forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge and the ball rolls behind square on the off side.
A flatter and quicker one on off. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Angles it on middle and leg this time. Pujara fends it to the leg side with soft hands.
Slower through the air and touch around off. Pujara opens the bat face a bit as he guides it towards cover-point.
Flatter and quicker on off. Pujara blocks it solidly from his crease.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! KL Rahul departs now and this is a very prouductive little period for Bangladesh! KL Rahul is absolutely gutted and punches his bat in frustration. Bangladesh players and their fans on the other hand are over the moon, big wicket. Lands it on a length and outside off. Rahul tries to drive it on the up and away from his body. However, the ball nips in a bit and catches the inside edge of his blade that knocks over the stumps. Bangladesh now have two wickets in this morning session.
Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Back of a length and around off. Kohli steers it towards gully.
Virat Kohli is off the mark! A fullish delivery, around off. Kohli drives it wide of mid off and takes a single.
Serves it fuller and on off at 137 kph. Pujara drives it back to the bowler.
Lands it on a good length, on off. Pujara blocks it solidly from his crease.
On a length, on middle. Pujara works it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Tossed up nicely on off. Kohli with a solid front foot block.
On off and bit fuller this time. Kohli takes hit front foot forwrad and blocks it again.

OUT! LBW! This is a huge wicket for Bangladesh! Taijul Islam is the man again! He has been bowling brilliantly in the last few overs and now after getting Gill, gets rid of arguably one of the greatest batters of this era. Taijul Islam lands it on leg and it is bit short and turns away. Kohli goes back and looks to defend it. However, the sharp turn beats him and hits Kohli on the back leg. Taijul Islam makes a very loud appeal as it looks quite plumb and the umpire too raises his finger. However, Kohli reviews it after consultation with Pujara but the UltraEdge shows no bat there. The Ball Tracking rolls and it also shows three reds. So, the original decision stays and India lose their third wicket.
Howout: lbw b Taijul Islam

Commentary: Tossed up delivery on off. Pant blocks it out.
Lovely delivery! This one is tossed up, around off. Pant skips down the track and the ball turns into him. Pant who tries to work it towards the leg side misses and gets hit on the pads.
Touch shorter and on off. Pant punches it to covers. Another wicket-maiden from Taijul Islam!
Good length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball on off, Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to the fielder at covers.
This one lands fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to backward point for one.
Fuller one angling it in, Rishabh Pant works it to mid-wicket. Dot.
Goes fuller again, on off. Rishabh Pant flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Bowls it outside off, Rishabh Pant moves forward and looks to slap it but gets a bottom edge as the ball rolls towards point. They collect one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Good length and on off, Rishabh Pant leans forward an pulls it hard in the gap through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant moves forward and defends it to mid off.
Another one on off, Rishabh Pant defends it to mid off again.
Tossed up on off, turning it in. Rishabh Pant looks to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball hits his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Outside off, Rishabh Pant flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller one this time, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to short covers.
Good length angling it in, Rishabh Pant defends it to covers.
Bowls it on off, Rishabh Pant taps it to covers and calls for a quick single but Cheteshwar Pujara sends him back.
Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant eases it to the man at point for one.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, slower too. Cheteshwar Pujara pulls it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Keeps it low and just outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and down leg, Rishabh Pant plays a lap sweep through fine leg for a boundary. Excellent timing on this.
SIX! Perfect timing. Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant shimmies down the wicket and lofts it over long on for a biggie. First one of the match!
Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant defends it to square leg.
Slightly shorter one, Rishabh Pant eases it to the man at square leg again.
Fuller and quicker too, Rishabh Pant flicks it to leg gully for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara punches it to deep covers for a brace.
Bowls it outside off turning it away, Rishabh Pant slaps it to point for one.
Bowls it down leg with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara reads it in the very end and blocks it to short leg. Lovely delivery!
Fuller and on off this time, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Excellent timing. Slower and outside off, Rishabh Pant cuts it in the gap through backward point for a boundary!
Another one outside off shaping it in, Rishabh Pant reads it well and lets it go.
Outside off again, Rishabh Pant knocks it to mid off for one. The ball did carry towards the right of the bowler but it wasn't a chance. They collect one.
Tossed up, on middle. Rishabh Pant defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Bowls it quicker and outside off, Rishabh Pant opens the face of the bat and guides it through third man for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Rishabh Pant flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara rocks back and cuts it in the gap through point for a boundary! Taijul Islam was not in control of his length here.
Fuller and on middle with a hint of turn, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to short leg.
Bowls it down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. That will be LUNCH on Day 1.
Good length and on middle, Rishabh Pant flicks it to square leg for one.

FOUR! A chance goes abegging. Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball carries to the right of the keeper. He just gets his glove to it as the ball races towards the third man fence for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it through towards the keeper.
This one lands outside off and nips back in. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but misses.
On a length and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms at it.
Fuller and outside off, Rishabh Pant leans and drives it towards covers for one.
Bowls it down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to backward square leg for a brace. Good running!
Keeps it bowling fuller, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to mid-wicket.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the mid-wicket region.
Tosses it up on middle and leg, Cheteshwar Pujara works it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly off the front foot.
Good length and outside off, Rishabh Pant looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Lucky that it didn't chop onto the stumps!
This one lands down leg, Rishabh Pant looks to flick it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant taps it to the fielder at covers. Dot.
Bowls it on middle, Rishabh Pant nudges it but finds the fielder at square leg. Four dots now.
Goes fuller and outside off, Rishabh Pant cuts it to backward point for one.
Outside off this time, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but misses.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, on off. Rishabh Pant hangs back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary! Fifty partnership comes up between Rishabh Pant and Cheteshwar Pujara and 100 up for India!
Fuller and on off, Rishabh Pant defends it to mid off.
Another fuller delivery as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Rishabh Pant taps it to the fielder at point.
Tossed up, on off. Rishabh Pant lunges and defends it solidly.
Fuller again as Rishabh Pant leans forward and defends this one to mid off.
Ebadot Hossain bowls it on a good length and outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.

This is poor from Bangladesh! Lands it on a length, on off. Pujara blocks it back to the bowler. However, Ebadot Hossain for no reason throws it back to the keeper and also fires it just over him and Nurul Hasan is not ready for it and the ball goes over him and a single is taken.
FOUR! Now, this is what happens when you give away easy singles. Short and wide outside off. Pant slashes at it and gets a boundary as the ball races away towards the point fence.
Back of a length, on middle. Pant works it to towards the leg side.
On the shorter side, on off. Pant blocks it solidly from his crease.
Lands it on a length, on off. Pant clips it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara skips down the track and works it to mid on.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara works it to square leg for a single.
SIX! What a shot! This is why he is so dangerous in Test cricket! A full toss on middle. Pant slog-sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.

OUT! BOWLED! Oh, Rishabh Pant is gone and once again a batter who was looking very comfortable in the middle, departs against a run of play. Mehidy Hasan strikes this time. This is touch shorter and angled into middle and leg from 'round the wicket. Pant goes back as he makes room to cut it. However, he is cramped for room and gets an inside edge onto his pad as he tries to chop it. The ball goes off his pads and hits the stumps and this is a crucial breakthrough for Bangladesh.
Howout: b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: FOUR! Finds the edge but Shreyas Iyer gets away with a boundary! This is tossed up and outside off. Iyer tries to push it towards the off side but gets an outside edge. Luckily for him, it goes just wide of the diving slip fielder for a boundary.
Low bounce now! Shortish and outside off. Iyer who hangs on the back foot gets beaten as the ball goes under his blade back to the keeper.
On a length, on middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket this time.
Back of a length and outside off. A harmless delivery and Pujara leaves it.
Nice short delivery this time, angling into the body at 136 kph. Pujara ducks under it.
On the shorter side again, on middle. Pujara blocks it from his crease to mid on.
Lands it on a good length and outside off. It is at 142 clicks and Pujara leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely played! Back of a length and around off. Pujara plays it with soft hands and deliberately opens the face of his blade and guides it between the slip fielder and gully for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. It turns in and Iyer works it left of short fine leg.
Touch shorter and on middle and leg. Iyer works it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Again the turn into the batter. It pitches on middle and turns in to hit Iyer on his pads as he looks to clip it towards the leg side. The ball deflects towards short fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
Lovely loopy delivery, around off. Pujara skips down the track and pads it away.
On the shorter side on middle. Pujara works it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on the pads. Pujara clips it to square leg this time. Another very good over from Mehidy Hasan.
Oh, beaten! Serves a good-length delivery, outside off. It seams away after pitching and Iyer pokes at it tentatively but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Goes fuller and around off. Iyer drives it through cover-point for a couple.
Beauty! Cuts him into half this time! Lands on a good length and it comes into Iyer this time. He is stuck on his crease and gets beaten on the inside edge as he tries to block it.
Back of a length, on middle. Iyer works it towards the leg side.
Back of a length, on middle. Iyer is more solid this time in his defence.
Goes fuller and outside off. Iyer drives it firmly but straight to the cover fielder.
Tossed up and loopy delivery on middle. Pujara is beaten by the flight as he skips down the track and misses his flick shot to get hit on his pads.
Touch shorter and on middle. Pujara works it towards the leg side.
Flighted delivery, on off. Pujara blocks it from his crease.
Goes fuller and on off. Pujara drives it right of the bowler. He stops it with a dive.
Tossed up again on off. Pujara shmmies down the track and works it to mid on.
On the shorter side, on middle. Pujara goes deep in his crease and works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and around off. Iyer rides the bounce and dabs it towards the off side.
Back of a length and angling into off at 137 kph. Iyer fends it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller and on the pads. Iyer flicks it to mid-wicket this time.

A fullish delivery, outside off. Iyer drives it to deep cover. The batters take single and decide to take the second run as well. The throw comes in at the bowler's end and Pujara puts in a dive to make his ground. There is no one behind the stumps and the fielder misses the direct hit and India get two more runs on the board. They needed somone to be at the stumps to take the throw and whip the bails off.
Back of a length and around off. Iyer dabs it towards point.
Lands it on a length, on off. Iyer fends it solidly from his crease.
Tossed up and outside off. Pujara skips down the track and gets hit on the pads as he tries to defend it. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Fuller and slower through the air and Pujara blocks it out.
Turning into middle and flatter. Pujara defends it from his crease.
Lovely loopy delivery on middle. Pujara manages to defend it towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara nudges it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Bowls it quicker and on middle. Pujara blocks it towards short fine leg. A maiden from Mehidy Hasan.
Goes fuller and on off. Iyer drives it off the outside half of his blade to point.
Lands on a length, on off. Iyer blocks it from his crease.
Tentative to say the least! Ahmed bowls it on a length, on middle. Iyer tries to work it towards the leg side but gets a leading edge. Luckily it falls way short of mid on.
Back of a length, on off. Iyer blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle. Iyer works it wide of mid on and the fielder at mid on makes a good stop diving to his right.
Nice accurate bowling this. Lands it on a length, on off. Iyer is right behind to block it.
On the shorter side, on middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up delivery on off. Pujara reaches the pitch of the ball and defends it towards the leg side.
Fraction short and on middle. Pujara goes back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Goes fuller and on off. Iyer takes a big stride out and pushes it towards the leg side.

Iyer gets two runs but Mehidy is bowling superbly here! This is just short of full length, around off. Iyer tries to defend it but gets an inside edge that goes past the stumps towards fine leg for a couple.
Flighted delivery on off. This time Shreyas blocks it from his crease.
On a length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller this time, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to backward square leg for a brace.
Good length just outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to short covers.
Fullish delivery on off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara rocks back and guides it through third man for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it away.
Tossed up, on middle. Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards Mehidy Hasan.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the mid on region.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller one and on off, Shreyas Iyer shimmies down the track and launces it over mid on for a boundary!
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer eases it to short covers.
Tossed up, on leg. Shreyas Iyer flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
FOUR! Shreyas Iyer is showing some intent here. Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer rocks back and cuts it in the gap through cover-point for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to short covers.
Another fuller one, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to covers.
Tosses it up on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Outside off, this is defended towards point.
Another fuller delivery with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it to point.
Bowls it on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it back towards the bowler who gets his hand to it. A maiden from Taijul Islam.
Bowls it on middle, Shreyas Iyer moves across and paddles it to short fine leg for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, Shreyas Iyer taps it to the fielder at mid on.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer lunges and defends it solidly.
This one lands down leg, Shreyas Iyer eases it to the mid on fielder.
Slightly shorter one, on leg. Shreyas Iyer works it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer eases it to mid off. Dot.
Outside off with some turn, Shreyas Iyer looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Close!
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer drives it to covers for one.
Tossed up, on middle with some turn. Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward and defends it away.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg for one.
Over the wicket, 87 kph. Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg. Dot.
Bowls it on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Outside off this time, Cheteshwar Pujara slaps it through deep point. The fielder does well to chase it. They collect three runs.
Another one outside off as Shreyas Iyer steers it to point for a brace.
Bowls it on off, Shreyas Iyer knocks it to mid on for one.
Fuller one on off, 86 kph. Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to mid-wicket.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Shreyas Iyer eases it to the fielder at mid off.
Another fuller delivery as Shreyas Iyer defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on off with some turn, Shreyas Iyer lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer leans forward and defends it to covers.
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer eases it straight on the toes of the silly mid off fielder. Dot.
This one lands down leg, Shreyas Iyer clips it to deep backward square leg for three runs.
Tossed up, on middle. Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, slower too. Shreyas Iyer looks to drive it but misses.
Bowls it on off, Shreyas Iyer lunges and defends it away.
Fuller one on the stumps, Shreyas Iyer defends it to the fielder at mid on.

DROPPED! Tough chance for the keeper though. Touch shorter and around off. Iyer tries to cut it but is cramped for room. The ball goes off the outside edge to keeper. However, Nurul Hasan drops it. The ball deflects off his gloves and rolls towards the slip fielder.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer taps it to point. Cheteshwar Pujara wanted a single but Shreyas Iyer sends him back.
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Another one on off with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to silly mid off.
Bowls it on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to mid on.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid off.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to the fielder at mid on.
Tosses it up on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara clips it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer defends it to point.
Bowls it on off, Iyer drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
On middle this time, Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Shreyas Iyer defends it to the mid on fielder.
Fuller and on off, 85 kph. Shreyas Iyer taps it to the fielder at mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara drives it to mid off this time.
Bowls it quicker and flatter on off. Pujara blocks it out.
That's a peach of a delivery! Flighted delivery, pitches just short of full length, on off. It turns away after pitching and the ball beats Pujara's blade as he tries to defend it.
An arm ball this time on middle. Pujara tries to defend again but gets an inside edge that goes past short fine leg.
Tossed up again on middle. Pujara with a solid block off the front foot.
Fuller and on off. Pujara drives it to covers. Brilliant over again.
Slower through the air on off. Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker and fuller. Iyer drives it to covers.
FOUR! Lovely shot and it brings up the fifty partnership! Tossed up, around off. Iyer plays a lofted cover drive and plays it in the gap towards the extra cover fence,.
A flatter delivery on off. Iyer blocks it out.
Touch shorter and turning away from off. Iyer shapes up to cut it but then decides to block it out.
Fires an arm ball on middle. Iyer is solid in his defence again.
Tossed up and around off. Pujara drives it to covers.
Flighted delivery on middle. Pujara tries to defend it but gets the inside edge past the short leg fielder.
Another lovely loopy delivery on off. Pujara fends it off the outside half of his blade.
Slower through the air again and tad around off. Pujara opens the face of his blade and plays it with soft hand and takes a single to short third man.
Fires it quicker and on middle. Iyer blocks it towards the leg side.
Changes his pace and bowls it slower through the air, on off. Iyer gets well forward to defend it.
Shorter in length, on off. Pujara punches it to short cover.
Slower through the air and touch short, on off. Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Lovely loopy delivery on off at 86 kph. Pujara fends it off the inside half of his blade.
Inside edge and bit of mix-up as well. Angles it on middle. Pujara tries to defend it but gets an inside edge that loops up a bit towards the leg side.
Slower through the air and around off. Pujara makes a solid block now.
Maiden!  Fires it quicker and flatter on off. Pujara blocks it out off the front foot.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Iyer with a good stride forward to block it.
Flighted delivery again on off. Iyer fends it off the front foot nicely again.
Serves it fuller and quicker on middle. Iyer drives it to covers.
Touch shorter and on off. Iyer goes deep in his crease and pushes it towards the off side.
On the shorter side again and around off. Iyer punches it left of long off for a couple.
Nice loopy delivery on middle to end the over. Iyer though is equal to the task and blocks it out.
Starts off with a full delivery on middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter in length, on middle. Iyer works it to deep square leg for a single.
Bit of mix-up but no damage done!  Tossed up delivery on off. Pujara reaches the pitch of the ball and works it to square leg. He looks for a single but Iyer sends him back.
Angles a quicker delivery on middle. Pujara works it towards the leg side and takes a single this time.
Tossed up nicely on off. Iyer blocks it off the front foot nicely.
FOUR! Good shot to end the session! A half-volley, outside off. Iyer takes a big stride forward and creams it through the extra-cover region for a boundary. That will be Tea on Day 1!
Ebadot Hossain starts off with a good-length delivery, outside off. Pujara leaves it alone watchfully.
Serves it fuller and on off at 137 kph. Pujara drives it to mid off this time.
Lands it on a length and angles it on off at 133 kph. Pujara with a solid block off the front foot.
On a length and on off at 135 kph. Pujara fends it out calmly again.
FOUR! Punched away! Short of good length and outside off. Pujara quickly transfers his weight on the back foot and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Pujara defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed up on middle. Iyer drives it to covers.
On the shorter side and at 78 kph. Iyer goes back and blocks it.
Pitches it outside off and it turns away further. Iyer goes back again and chops it to point.
Slower through the air on off. Iyer blocks it off the front foot.
Great delivery! A loopy delivery that pitches on middle and just short of full length. Iyer gets forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball turns away sharply.
A flatter delivery on off. Iyer fends it off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Pujara works it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Angles a length delivery on leg. Pujara clips it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Glorious shot, typical Shreyas Iyer shot! A fullish delivery, outside off. Iyer leans forward and drives it uppishly towards the cover fence for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off at 134 kph. Iyer blocks it from his crease.
Serves it fuller and around off. Iyer drives it to short cover and the fielder there half-stops as the ball rolls to mid off.
A yorker, around off at 137 kph. Iyer manages to dig it out towards the off side.

FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara gets to his fifty in style! Another gritty knock for the Indian number 3! 34th fifty for him in Test cricket. This man just knows how to find ways to score runs but he will like to get that century now which has been missing for a long time. Shortish and outside off. Pujara rocks back and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Now, he brings out a pull shot! It is short and on middle. Pujara goes deep in his crease and pulls it towards the square leg fence for a boundary.
Tossed up delivery on off. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Angles it on the pads this time. Pujara works it wide of square leg for a single.
Tossed up and on off. Iyer gets well forward to block it.
Another flighted delivery on off. Iyer gets a big stride forward and defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara gets in two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Another one outside off as this is defended towards covers.
Bowls it down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to square leg.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara rocks back and punches it to covers for one.
Slightly shorter turning it in, quicker too. Shreyas Iyer guides it to backward point for one.
Bowls it on middle, Shreyas Iyer defends it to mid off.
Slightly shorter and on off, Shreyas Iyer knocks it to mid on for one. He moves to 47.
Fuller one and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara clips it to square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Another fuller ball, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it to the fielder at mid on.
Bowls it on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fifty up for Shreyas Iyer. Slightly shorter and on off, Shreyas Iyer knocks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. His 4th Test fifty in 10 innings!
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer defends it solidly.
Another fuller delivery as this is played towards covers.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
Flighted around off, Iyer pushes to short cover. Dot.
Fuller one on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Another fuller one, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to square leg for one.
Tosses it up on middle, Shreyas Iyer clips it to square leg for one.
Keeps it bowling fuller, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to the mid-wicket fielder.
This one lands on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to mid on.
Similar to the last delivery, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to mid on again.
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer looks to slap it but gets a bottom edge towards short covers.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
Fuller and wide outside off, Iyer drives through the covers for a single.

Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer eases it to covers and calls for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the non striker's end and scores a direct hit. The on-field umpire takes the decision upstairs. However, replays show that Shreyas Iyer was well in.
Tossed up nicely on off. Iyer fends it off the front foot.
On off, defended out.
Fuller and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it away.
Outside off, this is defended towards mid off.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara works it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer defends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer taps it to covers for one.
Outside off again, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it down leg, Shreyas Iyer looks to flick it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, outside off. Shreyas Iyer looks to cut it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer lunges and defends it away.
This one lands on off, Shreyas Iyer taps it to the cover fielder.
Outside off this time, Shreyas Iyer defends it with soft hands towards slips.
Another one outside off, Shreyas Iyer defends it to gully. A maiden from Shakib Al Hasan.
Fuller one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to deep mid-wicket for three runs. 100 partnership up between Cheteshwar Pujara and Shreyas Iyer now!
Fuller again, Shreyas Iyer defends it to covers.
Bowls it on middle, Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Shreyas Iyer eases it to covers.
On off turning it away, Shreyas Iyer looks to defend it but misses.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer shimmies down the wicket and heaves it over mid-wicket for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara punches it to covers for one.
Outside off, this one kept a tad low. Shreyas Iyer knocks it to long off for one.
Bowls it on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Bowls it down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to the fielder at mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
Bowls it on middle, Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Shreyas Iyer defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer flicks it but finds the fielder at backward square leg.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Overpitched and on off, Shreyas Iyer shimmies down the wicket and heaves it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on middle, Shreyas Iyer defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Pujara is again solid in defence.
On the shorter side, on off. Pujara goes back and punches it to covers.
Angles a quicker one on the pads. Pujara works it to square leg but still no run.
Touch slower on middle. Pujara defends it off the inside of his blade towards the leg side.
Bowls it on the shorter side and it keeps bit low. Pujara is on the back foot to play it but manages to get his bat down in time.
A fuller delivery on off at 90 kph. Iyer fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it quicker on middle. Iyer works it to mid-wicket this time.
Touch short and turning into middle. Iyer works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara skips down the track and clips it left of mid-wicket.
Fires it quicker and flatter on off. Pujara blocks it solidly from his crease.
Tossed up, on middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket but fails to find the gap again.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Iyer drives it to long off for a single.
Slower through the air and on middle. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it quicker and on off at 88 kph. Pujara is solid in his defence.
FOUR! Short and punished! Shakib Al Hasan with a half-tracker on off. Pujara rocks back and pulls it firmly towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fires it quicker and on off. Pujara with a block off the front foot.
Keeps it on the same line and length and Pujara is again solid on his defence.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Iyer gets across to his right and scoops it to short fine leg for a single.
Angles a flatter delivery on middle. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off. Pujara again with a solid block.
Touch shorter and turning into middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up this time on middle. Pujara clips it to mid-wicket again.
Drfits on the pads and Pujara just tucks it fine towards the fine leg region for a couple.
Tossed up on middle. Iyer drives it to mid on this time.
Slower through the air, on middle. Iyer with a solid block off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on off. Iyer drives it to long off for a single.

Bit of confusion between the batters but no damage done! On middle and fuller. Pujara clips it to square leg and looks for a single. Iyer takes a few steps forward and denies the single. Pujara gets back to his crease quickly.
FOUR! This time in the gap! Tossed up on middle. Pujara shimmies down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and works it past square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off. Iyer drives it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller and on middle. Iyer works it to mid-wicket this time.
On the shorter side, on middle. Iyer works it off the back foot to the leg side.

Oh, my word! Ebadot Hossain has dropped a sitter! This one is tossed up on middle. Iyer dances down the track and tries to clear the mid-wicket fence. However, he fails to get enough distance and ends up hitting it straight to the deep mid-wicket fielder where Ebadot Hossain drops it.
Fires it quicker on off. Iyer with a solid block this time.
Loopy delivery on off. Iyer fends it off the front foot calmly.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tossed up on off. Pujara skips down the track, makes it a full toss and drills it down the ground for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and on off. Pujara defends it again nicely.
Gives some more flight and bowls it around off. Pujara blocks it towards the off side.

Sharp turn! Pitches it on middle and just short of full length. Pujara presses forward to defend it but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of his blade. Lovely bowling. Bit of appeal too but nothing serious.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara gets to the pitch of it and blocks it out.
A quicker delivery on off. Iyer fends it calmly.
Goes fuller and on middle. Iyer clips it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Pujara is finding boundaries with ease now! Shortish delivery and around leg. Pujara goes back and half-pulls it towards the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara skips down the track and works it towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on middle from 'round the wicket. Pujara tries to defend it but the turn and bounce produces an inside edge onto the pads.
Tossed up, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up delivery on off. Pujara with a solid block off the front foot.
Tossed up again on middle. Pujara skips down the track and works it to mid on.
Uses his feet again and works this full delivery on middle to wide of mid on.
Touch shorter and outside off. Pujara chops it towards the off side.
Angles a flatter delivery on middle. Pujara with a solid block from his crease.
Fires it quicker and flatter again sliding into middle. Pujara fends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Iyer with a block off the front foot.
Shorter in length, on off. Iyer makes room and mistimes his cut shot to the bowler.
FOUR! This time he cuts it quite well and 250 up for India! Short and outside off. Iyer rocks back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle from 'round the wicket. Iyer works it towards the leg side.
Flatter and quicker on off. Iyer blocks it out solidly.
On the shorter side, around off. Iyer tries to cut it but is cramped for room and ends up hitting it to mid off.
On a length and down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick it but misses.
Good length angling it in, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Bowls it on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer knocks it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Another fuller delivery, Shreyas Iyer defends it to mid off again.
Nice and full, outside off. Shreyas Iyer drives it to covers for one.
Tossed up and on off, Shreyas Iyer eases it to long off for a single.
Another one outside off, this is played towards point for one.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it solidly.
Bowls it fuller again, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it away.
Keeps it bowling fuller, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter, outside leg. Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer knocks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer pulls it to mid-wicket for one.
On a length and outside off shaping it away, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but misses.
Outside off shaping it away, Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms at it.
Another one just outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara reads it well and lets it go.
Slightly shorter one, Shreyas Iyer punches it straight to the fielder at short covers. Oh, its a no ball for overstepping.
This one lands outside leg, Shreyas Iyer leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Shreyas Iyer lets it go.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer opens the face of the bat and guides it to covers for one.
Back of a length angling into the pads. Pujara misses a tuck and gets a hit onto the pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The players have a discussion and decide not to review it.

Oh my word! What has happened here? Shreyas Iyer gets a lifeline. On a length and on off and it nips back in sharply. It bounces a bit low as well and Shreyas Iyer looks to block it but misses and the ball kisses the off pole but the bail stays on top. For a moment, the bail did fly, but it came back to sit in its normal position! How lucky is that? The Bangladesh players did celebrate for a while but stopped immidiately.
Back of a length and on middle. Iyer works it towards mid-wicket and takes a single. There is a bit of confusion regarding the second run but they decide to settle for a single.
Fuller and on off, Shreyas Iyer drives it to covers for one.

OUT! TIMBER! Taijul Islam finally gets the big fish. Fuller and on and off with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend it but misses completely. The ball rattles over the stumps and Cheteshwar Pujara makes his way back into the hut after a great knock. He walks out at 90!
Howout: b Taijul Islam

Commentary: A fuller delivery, outside off. Patel leans forward and drives it to covers.
Tossed up, on off. Patel fends it off the front foot.
Just shorter and quicker on middle. It keeps very low this time but Patel is aware enough to get his bat down just in time. Have to say, he played it well in the end.
Tossed up delivery on off. Patel with a solid front foot defence.
On a length and around off. Iyer drives it on up and towards the cover fielder.
Shorter in length and outside off. Iyer punches it to deep point for a single.
On a good length and angles across the left-hander. Patel leaves it alone.
Comes 'round the wicket and lands a fullish delivery, outside off. Patel leaves it calmly.
Goes fuller and on middle. Patel drives it to mid on this time.
Shorter in length and outside off. Patel punches it to deep point for a single.
Fires a flatter delivery on middle. Patel works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter in length and around off. Patel punches it through covers for a couple.

Turning into leg and Patel tries to defend it but gets rapped on the pads. However, it is clearly drifting down leg. So, the umpire remains unmoved even after a very loud appeal. Oh, the replays show that there was actually an inside edge on the pad and the fielder at short leg after catching it did appeal. However, Bangladesh did not take the review!
Fires a flatter delivery on off. Patel fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it on middle and leg and Patel goes back and blocks it out.
Tossed up and around off. Patel blocks it off the front foot.
Lands it on a length, on off. Iyer defends it from his crease.
On the shorter side and around off. Iyer punches it to deep point for a single.
On a length and around off. Patel punches it to covers.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Overpitched delivery and around off. Patel leans forward and creams itt hrough covers for a boundary.
A low full toss on middle from 'round the wicket. Patel drives it to mid on this time.
Bowls it full and down the leg side. Patel tries to clip it but misses. Nurul Hasan though dives to his right and half-stops it. So, the batters take a bye.
On the shorter side, on middle. It keeps a bit low and Patel manages to work it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A flatter delivery on off. Iyer blocks it from his crease.
Tossed up nicely on off. Iyer with a solid defence off the front foot.
A bit quicker on off. Iyer pushes it towards the off side with soft hands and takes a single.
Tossed up on off. Patel easily knocks it down to long on for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on middle at 82 kph. Iyer defends it off the front foot towards the leg side.
FOUR! Nicely played!  Hasan gives it some air, on middle and it is an overpitched delivery. Patel drives it beautifully past the bowler for a boundary.
Touch shorter and on off. Patel fends it out.
On the shorter side again on off. Patel goes deep in his crease and blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle. Patel gets big stride forward and defends it.
Angles it quicker and flatter on middle. Patel blocks it out nicely again.

OUT! LBW! Wicket of the last ball of the day! Axar Patel would be gutted here but this is exactly what Bangladesh needed to make things bit even at the end of this day. Mehidy Hasan comes 'round the wicket and bowls a slider on middle and leg. Patel comes forward to defend this last delivery but misses and gets hit on the pads. Mehidy Hasan and Bangladesh players make a huge appeal and up goes the finger! Both Patel and Shreyas Iyer does not look confident but Axar Patel takes the DRS at the last moment. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat there and then the Ball Tracking confirms that he is gone as the ball just clips the leg stump and it is umpire's call on wicket's hitting. Patel was lucky few overs back but now it is all over for him. India are 278/6 at Stumps on Day 1!
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Shortish and outside off. Iyer tries to cut it. There is a bit low bounce and turn too and Iyer manages to chop it towards backward point for a first run of the day.
Tossed up, around off. Ashwin fends it off the outside half of his blade towards the off side.
Tossed up again on off. Ashwin with a front foot defence again.
Touch shorter and on middle. Ashwin goes back and blocks it out.
Goes shorter again and on middle. Ashwin goes deep in his crease and punches it to mid on this time.
Serves it fuller and on off. Ashwin drives it but straight to mid off. Good accurate first over from Taijul Islam!
Back of a length and around off. Iyer punches it to cover-point for a single.

Good delivery! Serves it on a length, on off and it nips back in sharply. Ashwin tries to defend it but gets beaten as the ball hits him on the pads. There is an appeal but it seems too high and maybe going down leg too. As a result, the umpire is not interested.
A bit of low bounce! On a length and outside off. Ashwin tries to defend it from his crease but the ball goes through to the keeper from under his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Ashwin punches it to covers this time.
On a length and outside off. Ashwin drives it towards sweeper cover for a single.
Lands it on a length, on off. Iyer with a solid defence from his crease.
On off and quicker. Ashwin goes deep in his crease and pushes it to point.
Fires a quicker one on middle. Ashwin punches it to mid on.
Slower through the air, on off. Ashwin fends it off the front foot.
Lovely delivery! Loopy delivery on off. Ashwin tries to defend it but the ball turns. It catches the outside edge of Ashwin's blade and goes towards short third man where a single is taken.
Bowls it a bit quicker but fuller again and Iyer blocks it out.
Touch on the shorter side, on middle. Iyer works it to square leg and Iyer looks for a single but is sent back by Ashwin.
On a length and drifts on the pads. Ashwin clips it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Short and way down the leg side. Iyer lets it go and the ball dips onto the keeper but he makes a good stop with a dive.
On the shorter side again and around off at 136 kph. Iyer is tentative in his puch towards the off side and gets beaten.
Fuller length angling in, Shreyas Iyer flicks it straight to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length and outside off at 141 kph. Iyer punches it to sweeper cover for a single.

Ebadot Hossain lands it just short of good length and it is angled around off. Ashwin tries to defend it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and the ball goes towards the keeper. There is an appeal for an LBW though but the umpire is not interested. Shakib Al Hasan takes the DRS though after some consultation. The UltraEdge shows no bat here with the Ball Tracking also shows that the impact is outside off. So, the original decision stays and Ashwin will continue.
A flatter delivery on middle. Iyer works it towards the leg side.
Bowls it quicker and flattter on off. Iyer blocks it out off the back foot.
Tossed up, on off. Iyer leans forward and defends it off the front foot.
Angles it on middle and Iyer gets well forward to block it again.
Good length angling in, Iyer goes back and defends it to the mid-wicket region.
Fuller on the stumps, Iyer defends it back to the bowler.
Angles a touch shorter delivery into leg. Ashwin tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good delivery, goes wide of the crease and angles a short delivery on middle. Ashwin rides the bounce and just about manages to defend it short and right of short leg.
Back of a length and around off. Ashwin punches it to deep point for a single.
Angles a shortish delivery on the ribs. Iyer plays it off the bounce to short leg.

Oh, dropped! The ploy to bowl short at Iyer almost worked there! Good short delivery on middle. Iyer takes it on and gets a top edge. The ball goes aerially towards fine leg and Das there reaches it and gets both hands to it but fails to hold onto it in the end. Single taken. Another life for Iyer.
Back of a length, on middle. Ashwin works it to fine leg for a single. Mehidy Hasan comes into the attack now.
Tossed up nicely on off to start. Ashwin with a front foot defence.
Bowls it quicker and on middle. Ashwin defends it again.
Slower through the air and on middle. Ashwin works it gently towards the leg side.
SIX! This time he uses his feet and gets a maximum! Tossed up delivery on off. Ashwin dances down the track and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
Touch shorter and on off. Ashwin blocks it out calmly.
Turning into middle and leg this time. Ashwin works it to fine leg.
Back of a length, on off. Iyer with a block from his crease.
There it is.... a bouncer again! It is around leg and Iyer ducks under it.
Keeps bowling it short again. On middle and Iyer sets up to pull it but then ducks under it.
Back of a length and it drifts down the leg side again. Iyer tries to flick it but misses.
Good length angling in, Iyer defends it to the mid on region.

OUT! TIMBER! Ebadot Hossain with a beauty! Shreyas Iyer departs and Bangladesh gets an important breakthrough. This one lands on a good length and is angled on off. However, it straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of Iyer's blade as he tries to defend it. The ball knocks over the of pole and must say the ploy to bowl short deliveries at Iyer played a part in this wicket. Iyer is neither forward nor back and pays the price. It has been a very good knock from him though but he needs to sort out his short-ball issue for future.
Howout: b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Tossed up and bit shorter. It bounces low and Ashwin manages to block it off the back foot.
On middle and bit fuller. Ashwin fends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle. Ashwin with a solid block off the front foot.
On the shorter side and turning into middle. Ashwin punches it to covers.
Lovely loopy delivery on off at 87 kph. Ashwin drives it back to the bowler.
Turns it into middle and leg. Good bounce there too and Ashwin who tries to work it towards the leg side gets hit high on his blade as the ball loops up in the air towards the leg side.

There is a loud apeal for a caught behind but the impire is not interested. Khaled Ahmed convinces his captain and Bangladesh take the DRS. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat there as there is a spike when the ball brushes his pads. So, the original decision stays and Kuldeep Yadav will continue.
Serves it fuller and outside off. Yadav tries to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it on a length, on off. Yadav with a solid block from his crease.
Serves it on a length and outside off. Yadav leaves it alone carefully.
A fulllish delivery and it is angled across the left hander. Yadav lets it go again.

An appeal for an LBW but it is too optimistic, clearly going down leg. Back of a length and around leg. Kuldeep Yadav tries to work it towards the leg side but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There is an appeal but no damage done.
Tossed up, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin drives it but fins the fielder at covers.
This one lans down leg, 83 kph. Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to mid on for a single.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav lunges and defends it away.
Similar to the last delivery, Kuldeep Yadav defends it to silly mid off.
Another dot ball as the fuller ball is again defended towards the silly mid off region.
On a length and just outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it back towards Khaled Ahmed.
FOUR! Finds the gap. On a length and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it in the gap through backward square leg for a boundary!
Good length on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it to short mid-wicket.
Another one on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin nudges it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket again.
Bowls it on off this time, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it straight towards the fielder at mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin guides it to point and scampers through for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin lunges and blocks it away.
This one lands on off, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up with some turn, Kuldeep Yadav looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Close!
Another fuller delivery as this is defended towards silly mid off.
Fuller again, on middle. Kuldeep Yadav defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off turning it away, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to the fielder at gully.
Slightly shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it to square leg. The fielder in the deep does well to stop it. The batters collect one.
On a length with some extra bounce, Kuldeep Yadav blocks it to the off side.
Shorter and outside off, Kuldeep Yadav leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Kuldeep Yadav leaves this one alone as well.
Shorter nad just outside off, Kuldeep Yadav doesn't bother at it and lets it go.
Play and a miss. Good length and outside off, Kuldeep Yadav looks to drive it but misses.
Fuller one and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to short fine leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, Kuldeep Yadav knocks it to mid on and gets off the mark. They collect one.
Outside off this time, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav defends it to point.
Bowls it outside off turning it in, Kuldeep Yadav steers it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it back towards the bowler.
Shorter one around off, Kuldeep Yadav fends it to mid on.
Good length angling in, around off. Kuldeep Yadav taps it to covers.
Bowls it outside off angling in, Kuldeep Yadav reads it well and leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter one, Kuldeep Yadav rocks back and pulls it into the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary!
On a length and just outside off, Kuldeep Yadav shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller one, on middle. Kuldeep Yadav defends it to the leg side.
Fuller one and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it on off, Kuldeep Yadav blocks it to silly mid off.
Fuller one on off, turning it away. Kuldeep Yadav looks to block it but misses.
Fuller one, on middle. Kuldeep Yadav defends it to mid off.
On off, defended out solidly.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Kuldeep Yadav defends it to silly mid off.
Bowls it on off, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to the mid off fielder.
Fuller and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Outside off this time, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it to the left of mid off for one.
FOUR! Perfect timing on this. Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav plays a reverse sweep through backward point for a boundary!
Slightly shorter this time, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to mid on.
Fuller and on middle, Kuldeep Yadav lunges and defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin comes down the track and defends it away.
Bowls it on off, Ravichandran Ashwin covers his line and defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin shimmies down the track and flicks it towards deep square leg for a couple.
Bowls it outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Another one on off as this is pushed towards mid off. Dot.
Bowls it outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin guides it to backward point for one.
This one lands just outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin guides it to point for one.
Fuller and on middle, Kuldeep Yadav lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it down leg, Kuldeep Yadav flicks it but finds the man at square leg.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the short mid-wicket region.
This one lands down leg, Kuldeep Yadav flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Bowls it outside leg, Kuldeep Yadav looks to flick it but misses.
Tossed up on off at 81 kph. Ashwin fends it off the back foot.
On the shorter side again and outside off. Ashwin goes deep in his crease and pushes it to point for a single.
Slower through the air and on off. Yadav calmly fends it towards the off side.
Goes fuller and on off. Yadav defends it solidly off the front foot.
Goes fuller and on off. Yadav is equal to the task and drives it to mid off.
Angles it quicker and on middle. Yadav fends it calmly towards the leg side.
Turn there! Tossed up, around off. The ball turns sharply and beats Ashwin on the outside edge as he tries to defend it.

Again some good turn and this time he finds the edge. Bowls it fuller on middle. Ashwin tries to push it but gets an outside edge. The ball rolls towards the third man region and the fielder who cuts it off fires a wayward throw and it hits the helmet behind the keeper. So the batters take two runs plus India are also awarded with five extra runs as the ball hits the helmet.
Tossed up and around off. Ashwin drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
An appeal for an LBW but it is turning down leg. It pitches on middle and turns in. Yadav tries to defend it but misses and gets rapped on the pads. The umpire is not interested in the appeal though.
Fuller one angling it in, Kuldeep defends it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Yadav with a front foot defence.
Shorter and quicker on middle. Ashwin punches it to long on for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Yadav fends it off the front foot.
A flatter delivery on off. Yadav blocks it out solidly.
Tossed up, on off. Yadav fends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Tossed up and outside off. Yadav lets it go.
Loopy delivery on middle. Kuldeep Yadav gets well forward to block it.
Fuller in length outside off as Ashwin drives it towards covers.
Tossed up on off stump as Ashwin pushes it back towards the bowler here.
Tossed up on middle. Ashwin fends it off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on off. Ashwin drives it but finds the fielder towards short cover.
Lovely loopy delivery on middle. Touch short of full length and Ashwin fends it off the front foot.
Bit quicker and fuller on off. Ashwin drives it back to the bowler. Another very accurate over from Taijul Islam!
Tossed up delivery on off. Yadav blocks it off the front foot.
Touch shorter and flatter on off. Yadav blocks it towards the off side.
Bowls it fuller and on the pads. Yadav works it towards the leg side for a single.
Angles it on the pads again and Ashwin clips it towards the leg side and takes a single.
Bowls it fuller and around off. Yadav drives it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on off. Loopy delivery and Yadav blocks it off the front foot.
Good delivery! Bowls it quicker and just short of full length on middle. Ashwin goes back to this delivery and just about gets a bat down in time. A bit of outside edge too.

Pitches it around leg and Ashwin is again back to the delivery that he could have played on the front foot. He tries to clip it but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Nurul Hasan, the keeper convinces Shakib Al Hasan and they take the review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat here. The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that it is umpire's call on wicket's hitting. So, the original decision stays. Ashwin will continue.
A flatter and quicker delivery on middle. Ashwin blocks it out.
Tossed up on middle. Ashwin skips down the track and mistimes his drive it to mid on.
A quicker delivery on middle. Ashwin blocks it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tossed up delivery on middle. Ashwin makes room, reaches the pitch of the ball and creams it through the extra-cover region for a boundary.
Fires it quicker and on the pads. Yadav clips it to fine leg for a couple.
Serves it quicker and fuller on middle. Yadav drives it to covers.
Tossed up on off. Yadav drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
On the shorter side, and turning into leg. Ashwin goes back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Nicely played! Tossed up and around off. Yadav drives it square off the wicket towards the off side and takes a single.
Tossed up on leg. Ashwin works it to square leg this time.
Fires a quicker delivery, that goes through with the arm on middle. Yadav fends it off the inside half of his blade.
Tossed up delivery on off. Yadav with a solid block this time.
Loopy delivery on off. Yadav fends it off the front foot nicely.
Touch shorter and outside off. Yadav leaves it alone.
Slower through the air and on off. Yadav defends it nicely again.
Flighted delivery again on off. Yadav is well forward to block it and does so with ease.
Goes fuller and outside off. Ashwin drives it towards deep cover for a single.
Pitches it on leg and it turns down the leg side. Yadav tries to work it towards the leg side but misses.
Flatter and quicker on off. Yadav fends it nicely off the front foot.
Goes fuller and on off. Yadav defends it again calmly.
Touch shorter and on the pads. Yadav clips it to backward square leg.
Bowls it quicker and flatter on off. Yadav is quick to spot it and goes back to block it out.
Bowls it on off, touch shorter of full length and Ashwin fends it off the front foot.
Tossed up again, on off. Ashwin defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
Bowls it quicker and on off.Yadav with a good front foot defence as Mehidy Hasan bowls it from 'round the wicket.
Yadav finds the gap! Touch shorter and around off. Yadav plays it late and opens his bat face as he guides it through the backward point region for a couple.
FOUR! Good shot and Kuldeep Yadav has shown some great skills with the bat here! Tossed up on middle. Yadav sweeps and sweeps it through the square leg region for a boundary.
Nicely blocked again! Hasan tosses this one up on off. However, though there is turn, it is a slow one and Kuldeep gets well forward to defend it out. That will be Lunch on Day 2!
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin covers his line and defends it away.
This one lands down leg, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to square leg for one.

Touch shorter, outside off. Kuldeep Yadav looks to cut it but misses. The Umpire checks for the stumping and on the way they first check for a caught behind. The UltraEdge shows a flat line and Kuldeep Yadav was well in too when they check for a stumping.
Bowls it outside off, Kuldeep Yadav reverse sweeps it towards third man for a brace.
Bowls it outside off, this one nips in a long way. Kuldeep Yadav looks to play at it but misses as the ball hits his thigh. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Bowls it on leg, Kuldeep Yadav flicks it to the man at square leg.
On a length and outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to the fielder at covers.
Another one just outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to play at it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it to square leg for one.
On a length and on off, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to covers for a quick single.
Good length again, Ravichandran Ashwin blocks it towards the mid on region.
Short ball, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it to square leg for one and keeps his strike in the next over.
Tossed up, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin defends it to silly mid off.
SIX! Fuller one, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin shimmies down the wicket and lofts it over long on for a maximum! He moves to 49 now.

Fifty up for Ravichandran Ashwin. Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin drives it to deep cover and takes a single. His 13th Fifty in Test cricket and it has been a very fluent knock. He has looked very comfortable right from the onset and just continues to grow in stature as an all-rounder.
Fuller again, this is defended towards the leg side.

Tossed up, on off spinning it in. Kuldeep Yadav looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down. Bangladesh goes for a review. Replay shows that it was fair delivery and the UltraEdge shows no spike. Ball Tracking shows it is just clipping the leg stump and it will be umpire's call on wicket's hitting. So, the original decision stays and Kuldeep Yadav will continue.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav blocks it solidly.
Bowls it on off, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Kuldeep Yadav fends it to the leg side.
Good length angling it in, Kuldeep Yadav defends it to covers.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav blocks it to point.
Bowls it on off, Kuldeep Yadav guides it but finds the fielder at backward point.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to point again.
Tosed up, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin drives it to covers for one.
Bowls it outside off, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to point.
FOUR! Fuller and on leg, Kuldeep Yadav gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary! Kuldeep Yadav gets his new highest score in Test cricket with this shot.
On middle, defended out.
Bowls it on off, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to mid on.
Another one on middle as Kuldeep Yadav defends this back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside leg, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to flick it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin fends it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin plays it with soft hands back towards the bowler.
Shorter one, Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it to mid-wicket for one. He wanted a second, but Kuldeep Yadav sends him back.
On a length with some extra bounce, Kuldeep Yadav knocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Kuldeep Yadav defends it to covers.
Fuller and on middle with a hint of turn, Ravichandran Ashwin covers his line and defends it away.
Bowls it down leg, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Fuller and outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin eases it to mid off for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Bowls it on off, Kuldeep Yadav gets on his knee and slogs it through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on middle, Kuldeep Yadav defends it to short mid-wicket.
On middle again, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to the mid on fielder.
On a length and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin knocks it towards the fielder at mid on.
Fuller and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller one angling it in, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Shorter and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it back towards the bowler.
Shorter one, slower too. Ravichandran Ashwin plays it with soft hands to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up on middle, Kuldeep Yadav defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on leg, Kuldeep Yadav eases it to short mid-wicket.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards mid on.
Goes fuller again, Kuldeep Yadav lunges and defends it away.
On off turning it in, Kuldeep Yadav covers his line and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Kuldeep Yadav knocks it to mid on for a quick single.
Fuller and on off, Kuldeep Yadav drives it to covers for one.
On middle this time, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it to covers.
Bowls it outside off with some turn, Ravichandran Ashwin looks to play at it but misses.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the off side.
Fuller length around off, Ravichandran Ashwin defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up and outside off. Yadav drives it off the outside half of his blade to deep backward point for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Ashwin skips down the track and pushes it to covers.
Touch shorter and on off. Ashwin goes back and pushes it to point for a single.
Goes fuller and turning into middle. Yadav works it towards the leg side with a turn.
Things are moving along quite smoothly for India now! Tossed up, on off. Yadav drives it towards wide of long off and comes back for the second run.
Bowls it on middle and fuller. Yadav sweeps it to deep square leg and takes a single to retain the strike. This partnership is now 91!
Well stop in the deep! Hasan with a full delivery on middle. Yadav sweeps it to deep square leg and the fielder there who is some yards inside the ropes dives and stops it.

OUT! STUMPED! Finally, a breakthrough for Bangladesh! Ravichandran Ashwin departs and India are eight down now. Ashwin makes his intentions clear quite early and dances down the track. Hasan cleverly pulls his length back and bowls it outside off. Ashwin still goes for a wild swing across the line but misses. Nurul Hasan behind the stumps collects it and almost forgets to whip the bails off. However, he does so after a pause and Ashwin who is well out of his crease has to walk back.
Howout: st Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: A flatter delivery on off. Yadav blocks it out.
SIX! Here we go...a biggie from Umesh Yadav! Tossed up on odd. Umesh Yadav kneels and slog-sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
A flatter delivery on off. Umesh Yadav punches it to covers.
On the shorter side and outside off. Umesh Yadav pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle. Umesh Yadav fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Umesh Yadav gets a big stride forward and defends it.
Shorter in length on middle. Umesh Yadav tries to pull it but mistimes it to mid on for a single.
Tossed up on leg. Kuldeep Yadav works it to square leg.

OUT! LBW! Now, Kuldeep Yadav departs and India have lost their ninth wicket now! Good knock from him and he has shown that he has all the skills to make some useful contributions with the bat in this level. Coming to the ball - It is a quicker one from over the wicket turnung into middle and leg. Kuldeep Yadav goes back and tries to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball bounces low and hits Kuldeep Yadav low on the pads. He looks out and Taijul Islam makes a loud appeal. The umpire too does not take much time to raise his finger but Kuldeep Yadav decides to take the DRS more in hope than anything else. The UltraEdge shows no bat here. The Ball Tracking then rolls and it shows three reds. The original decision will stay and Kuldeep Yadav has to walk back.
Howout: lbw b Taijul Islam

Commentary: FOUR! Siraj wastes no time and smashes it away for a boundary! Tossed up on middle. Siraj skips down the track, gets outside the line of the ball and lofts it towards the extra cover fence for a boundary.
SIX! Entertaining stuff this! Tossed up on middle. Yadav gets low and slog-sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. 400 up for India!
Short and outside off. Yadav tries to cut it but misses.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Yadav drills it to long on for a single.
Shorter in length, on off. Siraj blocks it off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Gone this time and India have been bowled out for 404! Siraj dances down the track and Hasan pulls his length back smartly. Siraj still tries to tonk it down the ground but miscues it completely. The ball goes high in the air towards long on where Mushfiqur Rahim runs forward and takes a good catch to give Mehidy Hasan his fourth wicket.
Howout: c Mushfiqur Rahim b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, Mohammed Siraj you beauty! He strikes in the first delivery of the innings and Shanto walks back for a golden duck! Siraj is on the money straightway and lands it on a good length and it seams away from the batter.
