Shanto tries to defend it but the angle of the delivery and the movement takes the outside edge of his blade and Pant does the rest as he dives to his left and takes a fine catch. Bangladesh in early trouble.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Serves it on a good length and outside off. Ali makes a watchful leave.
Bowls it fuller and outside off. Ali leaves it alone again.
Serves it on a length again and outside off. Ali decides to let it go again.
Goes fuller and on middle. Ali drives it rigth of mid on. Ashwin dives and half-stops it but the batters manage to take two.
On a good length and outside off. Ali lets it go as it is a harmless delivery outside off. Good start from Siraj!
Goes fuller and outside off at 139 kph. Hasan leaves it alone. Bit too wide outside off.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Bit of movemebt away from the batter and Zakir Hasan lets it go.
First run in Test cricket for Zakir Hasan! Touch short of good length, on off. Hasan defends it towards cover-point and takes a single.
Back of a length and around leg. Ali tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
On a good length, on off. Ali calmly defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Ali rides the bounce and punches it to covers for a single.
An outswinger just outside off, Yasir Ali looks to defend it but misses.
Another one outside off shaping it away, Yasir Ali shoulders arms at it.
Fuller one on middle, Yasir Ali defends it to short covers.
Goes fuller again, Yasir Ali flicks it to the fielder at square leg.
This one lands outside leg, Yasir Ali looks to flick it but misses.
Fuller one on leg, Yasir Ali flicks it to backward square leg for one. He keeps the strike for the next over.
Fuller one on off, Yasir Ali defends it to mid off.
Good length angling it in, Yasir Ali fends it to mid on.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Umesh Yadav strikes and once again the Bangladesh top order is failing to show the application and skills that is required at this level. Good length and outside the off stump, comes back off the seam. Yasir Ali looks to punch it but does so away from his body and gets an inside edge as the ball rattles the leg pole. Pressure piling up on Bangladesh batters now as they are two down in a jiffy!
Howout: b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Fuller and on leg, Litton Das block it to mid on.
Good length and on off, Litton Das plays it with soft hands towards the mid on region.
Goes down leg, Litton Das flicks it to backward square leg and gets off the mark.
Bowls it on leg, Litton Das flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and on off, Litton Das punches it to deep covers for a brace.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Litton Das defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Litton Das shoulders arms at it.
Fuller one on middle, Litton Das defends it to mid on.
Another one outside off shaping it away, Litton Das lets it go.
Fuller one on middle, Zakir Hasan knocks it down the ground towards mid on. The fielder is quick to collect it. Dot.
Good length and outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Shorter one on middle, Zakir Hasan ducks under it.
Fuller and on the stumps, Zakir Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
Outside off with some extra bounce, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone again.
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Litton Das lets it go.
Good length angling it in, Litton Das defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das blocks it to mid off.
Another one angling it in, Litton Das reads it well and defends it out.
On a length and on off, Litton Das guides it to backward point for one.
Another one angling it in, Zakir Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Litton Das defends it with soft hands towards mid off.
Fuller and on middle again as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Good length angling it into the batter, Litton Das blocks it solidly.
Another dot ball as this is again defended back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller one this time, on off. Litton Das rocks back and flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary!
FOUR! Back to back boundaries. Fuller and down leg, Litton Das uses the pace of the ball and helps it through fine leg for another boundary!
Bowls it outside off turning it away, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller one on middle, Zakir Hasan defends it with soft hands towards to short leg.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, Zakir Hasan defends it to silly mid off.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, Zakir Hasan rocks back and slaps it through point for a boundary!
Bowls it down leg, Zakir Hasan defends it to short leg.
On a length and on middle, Litton Das defends it back towards the bowler.
On off this time, Litton Das eases it to the man at mid on.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, on off. Litton Das hangs back and pulls it through mid-wicket fro a boundary!
FOUR! Another one. Fuller and on off, Litton Das opens the face of the bat and guides it through backward point for another boundary!
FOUR! Three boundaries in a row from Litton Das! Fuller and outside off, Litton Das stands tall and creams it through covers for another boundary!
Fuller and on leg, Litton Das defends it towards mid on. That will be TEA BREAK on Day 2.
Tossed up on middle. Zakir Hasan drives it to mid off this time.
Shortish length and it turns away outside off. Hasan goes back and punches it to point.

An arm ball this time! It slides into middle and leg and is touch shorter in length. Hasan fails to get any bat on it as he goes on the back foot and gets hit on the pads. However, it is drifting down leg and there is just a half-appeal that is denied by the umpire.
Tossed up and outside off and Hasan leaves it alone.
Quicker delivery on middle and leg. Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Das takes a stride forward and defends it towards the leg side.
Serves a fullish delivery, around off. It is angled across the left hander and Hasan leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Hasan dabs it towards the off side nicely.
Goes fuller and on off at 136 kph. Hasan drives it but straight to mid on. Not much swing so far for the Indian pacers but they have bowled good lines and lengths.
On a good length and it is angled across the left hander again. Hasan with an easy leave.
Nice shot! A fullish delivery on off. Zakir Hasan drives it right of mid off and Pujara runs to his right and stops it with a dive. Good stop and it is just a single.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Das with a solid block towards the leg side.
Fires a flatter delivery, around leg. Hasan tries to clip it towards the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan takes a big stride forward and blocks it out.
Big inside edge! A slider from Ashwin on middle. Hasan tries to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
A quicker one and a flatter delivery sliding on leg. Hasan goes back and tries to work it towards the leg side but misses again to get hit on the pads.
Slower through the air and on off. Hasan with a front foot defence.
Touch shorter in length and turning away, outside off. Hasan chops it to the cover fielder.
Back of a length and around off at 140 kph. Das dabs it towards backward point. Some banter between Siraj and Das!

OUT! BOWLED! The mind game seem to have worked here for Siraj! Certainly Siraj got into head of Das and this is a big, big wicket! A good-length delivery angling into off. Das tries to defend it but ends up not getting much forward and defends it onto the turf as the ball rolls back towards the stumps. Siraj is up with his celebration and Das who was looking so good before the Lunch walks back now. Bangladesh three down now!
Howout: b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: A bouncer to greet Rahim here. On middle and leg and Rahim ducks under it.
On a good length, on off. Rahim blocks it solidly towards the off side.
Serves a fullish delivery, on off. Rahim with a front foot defence.
Ends the over with a short delivery angling into middle and leg. Rahim ducks under it. Bangladesh are still 365 runs behind!
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan drives it to covers this time.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Hasan blocks it out off the back foot.
Lovely delivery, a straighter one that pitches on off and Hasan defends it off the inside half of his blade.
Good running! Tossed up on middle. Hasan works it wide of mid on for a single.
A carrom ball this time at 85 kph. Rahim blocks it from his crease.
FOUR! Mushfiqur Rahim is off the mark with his favourite shot! This is fuller on middle. Rahim kneels and sweeps it through the square leg region for a boundary.
On a good length, on off. Hasan dabs it to point for a quick single.
Angles a length delivery on the pads. Rahim clips it to backward square leg.
Serves a fulling delivery that is angled from wide of the crease to middle. Rahim blocks it from his crease.
Lands on a length, on middle. Rahim defends it solidly yet again.
FOUR! Well played! Back of a length and around off. Rahim rides the bounce and plays it late as he opens the face of his blade and guides it through the gully region for a boundary.
Goes fuller and angles it into off. Rahim with a good solid block this time.
FOUR! In the gap! Tossed up on off. Overpitched delivery and Hasan drives it bit uppishly but through covers in the gap for a boundary.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Hasan goes back and cuts it to cover-point.
Fires a quicker and shorter delivery on middle. Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Hasan gets well forward and fends it out.
Tossed up on the pads. Hasan clips it to the fine leg region and both the batters run two quite quickly. They initally set off for the third run as well but then Rahim sends Hasan back just in time.
Touch shorter and on middle. Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Goes fuller and on off. Hasan drives it straight to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mohammed Siraj gets his third wicket and gets rid of the debutant, Zakir Hasan! This is Siraj as his best. There is not much help for him in this pitch but he is still bowling with lot of heart and keeps on hitting those nagging lines and lengths regularly. Brilliant suff! This one lands on a good length and around off. Siraj bowls it from 'round the wicket and the ball just straightens after pitching. However, Hasan has a tentative poke at it and gets an outside edge and Pant behind the stumps takes a regulation catch behind the stumps. Zakir Hasan looked solid in the middle but has to walk back now and he is disappointed.
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Goes fuller and on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it firmly to mid off.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Shakib Al Hasan fends it towards the leg side.
Back of a length and around off. Shakib Al Hasan dabs it towards backward point and there is a slight misfield. So, the batters take a quick single.
Nice shape into the batter. Serves it full and angles it into off. Rahim defends it but the ball goes off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it back to the bowler.
A full toss, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and tries to work it towards the leg side. He gets an inside edge that goes towards short fine leg. Quite a risky shot from Shakib.
Tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to covers and gets a single.
Touch shorter and turning into off. Rahim goes back and defends it out.
Tossed up on off. Rahim sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan drives it left of the bowler but Ashwin stops it.
Bangs it short and on middle. Rahim ducks under it.
Serves it on a length, on off at 134 kph. Rahim blocks it from his crease.
Back of a length and outside off. Rahim guides it to point and the fielder there misfields a bit and a single is taken.
A fullish delivery from 'round the wicket. It is a slower delivery and Shakib Al Hasan ends up playing it early as he tries to work it towards the leg side. The ball goes bit uppishly towards mid on.
Bangs it short from 'round the wicket and angles it on middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan ducks under it.
Goes back to the full length again, on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to that short mid off placed for a uppish drive there. This time though it goes off the bounce to him.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to drill it but doesn't connect well. It goes towards Ravichandran Ashwin.
Bowls it on off, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it solidly.
This one lands on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Shakib Al Hasan taps it to silly mid off.
Fuller one, Shakib Al Hasan shimmies down the track to play at it but ends up defending it. Dot again.
Another one on off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim guides it to point for one.
On a length and on off, Shakib Al Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Cracker of a delivery! Good length and just outside off with some extra bounce, Shakib Al Hasan looks to block it but the ball goes past the outside edge of his blade. That was close!
Bowls it on leg, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to short leg.
Bangs a bouncer and on middle, Shakib Al Hasan ducks under it.
Bowls it down leg, Shakib Al Hasan looks to flick it but the ball brushes his thigh and rolls towards fine leg. They collect two leg byes.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim eases it to mid on.
Tosses it up on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Goes fuller again, Mushfiqur Rahim knocks it to mid on and scampers for a quick single.
Bowls it on middle, Shakib Al Hasan lunges and defends it away.

FOUR BYES! Fuller and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to slash it away but misses. Rishabh Pant fails to grab it as well as the ball keeps low and races away towards the third man fence for a boundary!
On off, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it back towards the bowler.
Good length angling in, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it solidly.
Fuller and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play at it but gets an inside edge towards short leg. They cross.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim slaps it towards deep point for one.
Bangs a bouncer on middle, Shakib Al Hasan ducks underneath it.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it towards the man at mid on.
Tossed up, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to backward square leg for one.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Kuldeep strikes in his second ball and gets the dangerous Shakib Al Hasan. Fuller and on leg turning it away, Shakib Al Hasan shimmies down the track and looks to work it against the turn but fails to get the desired connection. The ball catches the outside edge of his blade and Virat Kohli takes a good catch in the slip. Bangladesh are in all sorts of trouble here.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Nurul Hasan rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary!

Fuller and on off, Nurul Hasan looks to defend it but misses and gets hit on the pads and the ball lobs towards slip where the catch is taken. There is an appeal for both LBW and catch but the umpire remains unmoved. After a lot of consultation, India decide to not take a review.
A googly outside off, Nurul Hasan looks to defend it but misses. Close! Kuldeep Yadav is all over the Bangladesh batters here!

Fuller and on off which turns in, Nurul Hasan looks to defend it but misses and gets hit on his pads. A loud appeal for lbw but the umpire says NO. KL Rahul this time decides to take the DRS as Kohli seems very confident. The Ball Tracking shows that it was just clipping the leg pole and the umpire's decision stands. Oh, they decide to take another look for a catch here. Hang on! There seems to be some noise in the UltraEdge as the ball goes from close to the glove and bat to the fielder. However, the further replays show that the murmur in the UltraEdge was for something else and there is no glove or bat involved. So, it remains NOT OUT!
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim taps it to the man at mid off.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim guides it to point. Dot.
On a length and on leg, Mushfiqur Rahim flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Shorter and on off, Nurul Hasan swivels and pulls it through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on leg, Nurul Hasan works it to square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim lets it go.
Fuller and down leg, Nurul Hasan looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and rolls towards fine leg. They collect one.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Mushfiqur Rahim eases it to mid off.
This one keeps a tad low, on leg. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to square leg.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim sweeps it to fine leg for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on leg, Nurul Hasan rocks back and pulls it through square leg for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it back towards the bowler.
Another one on off, Mushfiqur Rahim eases it to the man at mid off.
Another fuller one turning in, Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend it but miscues it to mid-wicket. They collect one.
Bowls it outside off, Nurul Hasan taps it to covers. Dot.
Another one outside off as this is played towards the man at point.
Outside off again, Nurul Hasan guides it towards backward point for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim knocks it to mid on and scampers through for a quick single.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Nurul Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off turning it in, Mushfiqur Rahim eases it to point for one.
Fuller and on leg, this one keeps a tad low, Nurul Hasan blocks it away.

Fuller and on off, Nurul Hasan clips it uppishly towards mid on and it just falls short of Ravichandran Ashwin at mid on. Ashwin was slow to get off the block there and could have reached it had he been more proactive in his approach.
Fuller and on middle, Nurul Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, this is defended towards the man at point.
Bowls it on off again, Mushfiqur Rahim hangs back and defends it solidly.
Tossed p, on middle. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it solidly off his front foot.
Bowls it on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Another dot ball as this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller and outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim taps it to point. A maiden from Axar Patel.
Tossed up on off. Hasan defends it from his crease this time.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Hasan takes a big stride forward and defends it.
Driving length and around off. Hasan drives it to the cover fielder.
Appeal for an LBW but no damage done! This one is tossed up on middle and turns back in. Hasan tries to drive it but misses and gets hit on the pads. However, it is going down leg.
Loopy delivery on middle again. Hasan drives it bit uppishly but well short of mid on.
Touch shorter, on middle and it turns into Hasan. He goes back and works it towards the leg side.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Rahim plays it quite well off the back foot and keeps it out.
Goes fuller and around off. Rahim drives it without much timing to covers.
Loopy delivery on off. Rahim with a front foot defence.
Bowls it just outside off and Rahim blocks it off his pads as the ball deflects towards the slip fielder.
Bowls it flatter and quicker on off. Rahim with a solid front foot defence.
Touch shorter and on off. Rahim goes back and fends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kuldeep Yadav strikes again and that's a sharp catch from Gill at short leg! Bangladesh lose their sixth and India are all over Bangladesh now. On the shorter side and turning into middle and leg. Hasan goes back and tries to work it towards the leg side but does so uppishly and Gill at short leg is quite aware and takes a brilliant catch. Someone need to stay here with Mushfiqur Rahim.
Howout: c Shubman Gill b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Oh, a googly! This one goes the other way, class of Kuldeep Yadav written all over it. This one is tossed up, on off. Hasan presses froward to defend but the ball turns away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Pitches on length and it turns further down the leg side. Hasan lets it go.
Tossed up again this time on middle. Mehidy Hasan with a front foot defence.
Pitches it around off and it turns into Hasan. He blocks it towards the off side off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out again.
Touch shorter and outside off. The ball turns away sharply and Rahim lets it go.
Tossed up on middle. Rahim works it towards the leg side.
Touch shorter and on middle. Rahim works it past square leg for a single.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Mehidy Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter on off. Hasan pushes it to cover-point this time.
Again quicker and flatter on off. Mehidy Hasan with a solid defence off the front foot.
FOUR! A low full toss and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim sweeps it hard and through mid-wicket for a boundary!

OUT! LBW! Fuller and on off with good sharp turn into the batter. Mushfiqur Rahim looks to defend it but misses and the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal and the finger goes up immediately. Mushfiqur Rahim decides to go upstairs. Fair delivery and Ultra Edge shows no spike. Ball Tracking shows three reds and Mushfiqur Rahim has to make his way back into the hut. Bangladesh are now 7 down! This is a big blow, he was the man who was holding one end up and we might just see things folding out very quickly now.
Howout: lbw b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Bowls it on off turning it away, Taijul Islam looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller and on middle, Taijul Islam lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it on off, Taijul Islam eases it to the silly mid off region.

OUT! TIMBER! Kuldeep Yadav is all over Bangladesh batters here and Bangladesh soon go 8 down in a jiffy. Bowls a googly on off, Taijul Islam looks to cut it but ends up getting an inside edge as the ball rattles the stumps. Taijul Islam had no idea about that delivery. He was playing for the normal stock delivery which goes away but it came back sharply with good bounce and have to say, Kuldeep Yadav is turning out to be too good for these Bangladeshi batters.
Howout: b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Bowls it outside off, Mehidy Hasan slices it to backward point for a brace.
Bowls it on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it to mid off.
This one lands on middle, Mehidy Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Outside off this time, Mehidy Hasan looks to slap it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards slips. Dot.
Quicker and just outside off, Mehidy Hasan looks to defend it but misses. Close!
Bowls it outside off, Mehidy Hasan guides it to backward point. The fielder is quick to get it and restricts a single. Good fielding!
Fuller and on off, Ebadot Hossain defends it to mid off.
Bowls it outside off, Ebadot Hossain digs it to point for a brace.
This one lands down leg, Ebadot Hossain flicks it to square leg for one.
Goes outside off, Mehidy Hasan eases it to the man at point.
Slightly shorter one, on middle. Mehidy Hasan awkwardly defends it back towards the bowler.
SIX! Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan reads it well and slog sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum!
Fuller and on off, Ebadot Hossain taps it to mid off.
Bowls it outside off, Ebadot Hossain eases it to the fielder at point.
Another one outside off, Ebadot Hossain defends it with soft hands towards slips.
Fuller and on off, Ebadot Hossain eases it to mid on.
Quicker and outside off shaping it away, Ebadot Hossain looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on middle, Ebadot Hossain covers his line and defends it solidly.
Bowls it on middle as Mehidy Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller again and on middle, Mehidy Hasan lunges and defends it out.
Bowls it down leg, Mehidy Hasan defends it with his pads.
Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Another one outside off, Mehidy Hasan drives it. The fielder does well to stop it at covers. Dot.
On middle this time, Mehidy Hasan lunges and defends it away. This has been quite a spell from Kuldeep Yadav. He has shown all his range here.
Bowls it on off, Ebadot Hossain plays it with soft hands towards slips. Dot.
Another one on off, Ebadot Hossain defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Good shot. Tossed up, on off. Ebadot Hossain drills it through long on for a boundary!
On off with some turn, Ebadot Hossain defends it to silly mid off.
Outside off shaping it away, Ebadot Hossain looks to play at it but misses.
Bowls it on middle, Ebadot Hossain lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Outside off turning it in, Mehidy Hasan eases it to short covers.

FOUR! Fuller one turning it in, Mehidy Hasan doesn't read it well and looks to play at it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes between the keeper and the slip fielder and the ball races away towards the third man fence for a boundary!
Bowls it on middle and the ball turns sharply in, Mehidy Hasan misses it completely as the ball misses the leg pole and rolls towards fine leg. The batters collect two byes.
Fuller one outside off, Mehidy Hasan looks to play at it but misses and gets a hit on his pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Close!
Shorter and on off, Mehidy Hasan rocks back and cuts it towards backward square leg for a brace.
A flatter delivery on middle. Ebadot Hossain tries to defend it but misses and the ball brushes his pads and goes towards leg slip.
Tossed up, on off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it off the front foot.
SIX! Ebadot Hossain decides that he needs to get some runs here! This one is tossed up on off. Ebadot Hossain tonks it over long on for a biggie.
A loopy delivery, around off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air and on off. Ebadot Hossain with a front foot defence again.
Ashwin with a quicker and flatter delivery on middle. Ebadot Hossain blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls it on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it to the fielder at gully.
Bowls it on leg turning it away, Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan taps it to deep covers for one.
This one lands on middle and keeps a tad low, Ebadot Hossain reads it well and defends it.
Goes outside off, Ebadot Hossain looks to play at it but misses.
Bowls it outside off, Ebadot Hossain looks to defend it but misses and hits his pads. The ball lobs towards the man at slips. Dot.
Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan knocks it to mid on but doesn't take a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Mehidy Hasan lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan knocks it to mid on for one.
This one lands on off, Ebadot Hossain plays it with soft hands towards mid off.
This one lands down leg, Ebadot Hossain defends it to mid on.
Bowls it on leg, Ebadot Hossain blocks it to short mid-wicket. That will be STUMPS on Day 2.
Tossed up delivery on off to start with. Hasan fends it off the front foot.
Touch shorter and on middle. It turns in and Hasan goes back to work it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan goes well forward to block it.
A googly and around off. Touch shorter and Hasan defends it off the outside half of his blade.
Turns into Mehidy and it is quicker on middle. Hasan works it to mid-wicket.
Short and down the leg side. Mehidy Hasan tries to pull it but misses.
Starts off with a yorker-length delivery on off. Ebadot Hossain just about manages to block it out.
On a good length and outside off. Ebadot Hossain tries to push it but misses.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Ebadot Hossain hops and works it towards the leg side.

FOUR! Streaky runs but Ebadot Hossain and Bangladesh will take it! A fullish delivery, around off. Ebadot Hossain tries to drive it but gets a thick outside edge that goes off the thick outside edge through the gully region for a boundary.
Here comes the short delivery, on middle and it is quite well targeted. Ebadot Hossain though sways away from the line of the ball.
Beaten! On a good length and outside off. Ebadot Hossain tries to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tossed up on middle. Mehidy Hasan pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up nicely on off. Hasan with a front foot defence.
Flighted delivery, around off. Hasan tries to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. A stifled appeal but nothing serious.
Shorter in length, on middle. Hasan goes back and fends it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up, on off. Hasan skips down the track, goes outside the line of the ball and drives it towards the extra cover fence for a boundary.
Touch shorter and on middle. Hasan works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle. Hasan works it to fine leg and does not take the single.
Goes fuller and on off. Hasan drives it straight to mid off.
An appeal for an LBW but it is going down leg! On a length and angling into middle and leg. Hasan tries to clip it but misses and gets rapped up on pads.
On a length and it is on middle and leg again. Hasan works it towards the leg side again.
Back of a length and around off. Hasan punches it through point and takes just a single as the fielder cuts it off.
Lands it on a length, on off. Ebadot Hossain fends it from his crease solidly.
Tossed up and around off. Hasan skips down the track and tries to smash it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge towards the leg slip fielder.
Touch shorter and on middle. Hasan works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up delivery on off. Ebadot Hossain fends it off the front foot.
Quicker and flatter one off. Ebadot Hossain blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kuldeep Yadav gets a five-wicket haul! First Indian bowler to do so at this venue! This is pitched on middle and it turns into Ebadot Hossain on leg. He tries to clip it but manages to just tuck it to the left of the keeper where Pant moves to his left and takes a sharp catch. India are just one wicket away from bundling out Bangladesh! What a comeback this has been for Kuldeep Yadav in Test cricket!
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Tossed up, on off. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out.
Lands it on a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan fends it from his crease.
Bowls it short and around leg. Mehidy Hasan ducks under it at the last moment.
Serves a length delivery on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it from his crease.
Good delivery, that bounces sharply on off. Mehidy Hasan rides the bounce and just about manages to defend it.
On a length and around off. Hasan guides it to the third man region for a single.
Serves it full and drifts it down the leg. Ahmed tries to flick it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes left of the keeper where Pant makes a good diving stop.
Tossed up delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery and outside off. Hasan tries to drive it but misses.
Turning into leg from 'round the wicket. Hasan fends it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery that pitches on off and turns into Hasan again. He defends it onto the turf.
Slower through the air again on middle. Hasan works it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan is solid in his defence again.
Siraj with a short delivery on off. Khaled Ahmed sways away from the line of the ball at the last moment.
Fires a short delivery again on off. Khaled Ahmed keeps himself outside the line of the ball.
Back of a length, on off. Ahmed defends it aerially but just short and left of short leg.
Back of a length, on off. Khaled Ahmed fends it from his crease.
Goes fuller and on middle. Ahmed tries to clip it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Keeps it out! On a length, on off. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out solidly.
Tossed up and outside off. Hasan with a big stride forward defends it.
Touch shorter and on off. Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Hasan with a front foot defence.
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan tries to work it towards the leg side. The ball goes off the leading edge but falls short of the bowler.
FOUR LEG BYES! Mehidy Hasan dances down the track and Yadav tries to turn it down the leg side. Hasan adjusts his shot and the ball ends up brushing his pads and rolls towards the fine leg fence.
Shorter in length, on off. Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Fires a quicker delivery on off. Khaled Ahmed defends it back to the bowler.

There is an appeal for an LBW but the umpire denies it. India though take the review! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat there. The Ball Tracking then rolls and it shows that the impact is umpire's call. So, the original decision stays. Coming to the ball - It is just short of full length, on off. Ahmed presses forward to defend but the ball turns away and brushes his back leg and rolls towards the third man region.
A flatter delivery on middle. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out.
Quicker delivery on off. Khaled Ahmed with a block off the front foot again.
Shorter and quicker on middle. Khaled Ahmed blocks it out.

An arm ball delivery angling into middle. Khaled Ahmed tries to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. There is a big appeal from the bowler and the umpire raises his finger this time. However, Khaled Ahmed reviews it and the UltraEdge shows that there is bat there. So the decision is overturned.
Tossed up on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on off. Mehidy Hasan fends it from his crease.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Slower and on middle. Hasan skips down the track and tries to work it towards the leg side but gets hit on the pads.
Shortish and outside off. Hasan lets it go.
Takes the single! Tossed up on middle. Hasan skips down the track and pushes it to left of mid on for a single.
Quick and turning away on off. Hasan defends it off the outside half of his blade.
Tossed up on off. Hasan drives it to covers.
Slower through the air and on off. Hasan shimmies down the track again and drives it off the outside half of his blade to point.
Flatter delivery on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.

OUT! STUMPED! It's all over! Bangladesh have been bowled out for 150! This one is slower through the air and bowls it touch short on middle. Mehidy Hasan skips down the track and tries to loft it away. He misses and Pant behind the stump collects the ball and whips the bails off. Mehidy Hasan is way out of his crease.
Howout: st Rishabh Pant b Axar Patel

Commentary: Starts off with a fullish delivery on off. Rahul drives it towards the bowler calmly.
Keeps it full again on off at 136 kph. Rahul with a front foot block this time.
Goes fuller and around off. Rahul tries to drive it but the ball goes off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Rahul lets it go as he keeps his bat inside the line of the ball.
Goes fuller and on off with a hint of away swing. Rahul drives it off the outside half of his blade to covers.
FOUR! India and KL Rahul are underway with a boundary! Beautiful drive! Overpitched delivery, around off. Rahul drives and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.
Goes fuller and on off. Gill with a front foot defence.
Tossed up on off. Gill drives it to mid off this time.
Slower through the air, on off. Gill with a block off the front foot.
Keeps it on the same length and length and Gill is happy to defend it again.
Fires it quicker and on off. Gill blocks it out from his crease.

Tossed up on middle. Gill dances down the track and tries to loft it down the ground. However, he miscues it a bit and the ball goes high in the air but still good enough to take it well behind the mid off fielder. Two taken.
Shortish delivery on off. KL Rahul with a solid block from his crease.
On a length and around off. Rahul presses forward and just opens his bat face a bit. The ball runs through the gully region for a couple.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Rahul works it towards the leg side.
Back of a length and angling into the pads. Rahul clips it to fine leg for a single.
Hint of away swing again, on a length and around off. Gill steers it towards third man for a single.
Just short of good length and outside off. Rahul lets it go watchfully.

This one is tossed up on middle and leg and just short of full length. Gill presses foward to defend but misses and gets rapped up on the pads. A big appeal and the umpire raises his finger. However, Gill after consulting his partner takes the DRS. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat here. The Ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the ball is missing the stumps. So, the decision will be overturned.
A flatter delivery on leg. Gill trties to clip it but misses. The ball brushes his pads and rolls towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
Tossed up and around off. Rahul tries to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Flatter and quicker delivery on off. Rahul blocks it out.
Tossed up again, on off. Rahul fends it towards the off side.
Shorter in length, on off. Rahul punches it to mid off.
Serves a length delivery on off. Gill with a solid block.
Back of a length and angling down leg. Gill tries to clip it but misses.
Beaten! Nice delivery, on a good length and outside off. Gill tries to defend it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length and drifting into the pads. Gill works it to fine leg for a single.
Serves it on a length, on off. Rahul defends it towards point nicely.
A fullish delivery, around off. Rahul pushes it gently to covers for a single.
Tossed up nicely on off. Rahul drives it off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
Loopy delivery on off. Rahul drives it to left of the bowler who stops it.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle and Rahul blocks it from his crease.
Slower through the air, on off. Rahul skips down the track and fends it towards the off side.
Shortish and outside off, Rahul waits for it and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
A slider into middle and Gill presses forward off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side. A single is taken.
On a good length, on off. It keeps a bit low and Gill blocks it out.
Serves it on a length, on off at 133 kph. Gill with a front foot defence.
Goes fuller and on the pads. Gill flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul fends it towards the off side.
Serves it on a length and around off. Rahul with a gentle push towards the off side.
Serves it fuller and on off. Rahul drives it to mid off this time. Not much happening for Bangladesh bowlers here.
Tossed up on off. Gill with a solid front foot defence.
Fires it quicker and on off. Gill blocks it out again.
Slower through the air and outside off. Gill lets it go this time.
Pushes it quicker and fuller on middle. Gill drives it towards the leg side.
Slower through the air on middle. Gill skips down the track and drives it to mid on.
An arm delivery that comes through with the arm, on middle. Gill defends it off the inside half of his blade.
Back of a length and outside off at 137 kph. Rahul lets it go.
Bowls it short and on middle. Rahul pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on leg. Gill works it to deep square leg for a couple.
Back of a length and around off. Gill defends it towards deep point for a single.
Back of a length on off at 133 kph. Rahul pushes it to covers this time.
Goes fuller and on the pads at 130 kph. Rahul flicks it to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Tossed up, on off. Gill presses forward to defend but gets it off the outside half of his blade towards the third man region for a couple.
Beauty! Slower through the air and tad shorter of full length on middle. Gill tries to defend it off the front foot. However, the ball turns and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Loopy delivery on off. Gill looks to defend it again but this time gets an outside edge. The ball rolls towards the third man region for a couple.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Gill blocks it out.
Touch shorter and fires it quicker again. Gill goes back to defend it.
Loopy delivery on middle. Gill gets well forward to defend it towards the leg side.
Short delivery on middle. Rahul pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Gill works it to mid-wicket nicely.
On a length, on middle. Gill stays in his crease and just dabs it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on middle at 130 kph. Gill works it towards the right of mid on.
Back of a length and around off. Gill uses his wrists again and works it towards mid-wicket.
On the shorter side, on middle at 138 kph. Gill clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Gill skips down the track and just about manages to defend it towards the leg side.
Touch shorter and it turns away. Gill punches it to covers this time.
On the shorter side and outside off. Gill chops it to the point fielder.
Tossed up nicely on off. Gill makes room and drives it to long off for a single.
Bowls it fuller and outside off. Rahul drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Gill presses forward to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
No run.
Fires it bit quicker on middle. Rahul works it towards the leg side.
Slower through the air, on off. It goes straight with the arm and Rahul blocks it out.
Keeps it tight on off and flatter. Rahul with a front foot defence.
A fullish delivery on middle at 89 kph. Rahul works it to backward square leg from his crease.
Fires a quicker one on off. Rahul goes deep in his crease and defends it back to the bowler.
Gill skips down the track and Islam fires it on leg. Gill blocks it with his pads.
An arm delivery on middle. Gill defends it towards the leg side.
Shorter in length, on off. Gill blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up, on off. Gill skips down the track and pushes it towards the off side.
Flighted delivery again on middle. Gill with a solid block off the front foot.
Another maiden! Shorter in length and around off. Gill punches it to covers.
Tossed up delivery on off. Rahul works it towards the leg side.
Touch shorter and quicker on off. Rahul goes deep in his crease and punches it towards the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tossed up and outside off. Rahul leans forward and square drives it through cover-point for a boundary.
Pitches it on leg and it turns down the leg side. Rahul tries to clip it but misses. Nurul Hasan takes it towards the leg side and makes a loud appeal but they decide to not take the DRS.
FOUR! Second boundary in the over! Short and outside off. Rahul goes deep in his crease and chops it towards the point fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Rahul leans forward and works it to square leg with ease. That is Lunch on Day 3!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards mid off.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill eases it to short covers.
This one lands on middle, Shubman Gill covers his line and blocks it away.
Goes fuller again, this is defended towards mid off.
Slightly shorter one, down leg. Shubman Gill flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Good length, angling it in. KL Rahul knocks it to the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it on off, 131 kph. KL Rahul defends it back towards Khaled Ahmed.
Fuller and outside off, KL Rahul opens the face of the bat and guides it to point for one.
Good length angling it into the batter, Shubman Gill eases it to mid off.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Shubman Gill looks to drive it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball carries through the vacant gully region for a boundary!
On a length and on leg, Shubman Gill eases it to mid on for one.
Tossed up, in off. This is defended solidly.
Another fuller one as this is blocked back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller again, on off. Gill defends it solidly.
This one lands on off, Gill covers his line and blocks it away.
FOUR! Fine shot. This one lands on off, fuller in length. Gill gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, defended well.
On a length and on off, Rahul eases it to mid off. Dot.
Good length in the channel around off, KL Rahul defends it forward to the cover region. Oh, its a no ball for overstepping.
Slightly shorter and on off, KL Rahul fends it towards covers.
Fuller one this time, KL Rahul knocks it down the ground towards mid off for one.
FOUR! Easy pickings. On a length and down leg, Shubman Gill uses the pace of the ball and helps it through fine leg for a boundary!
FOUR! Another one into the gap. On a length and on off, Shubman Gill uses the pace of the ball and guides it through third man for another boundary!
Good length and outside off, Shubman Gill leaves it alone. Oh, its a no ball for overstepping.
Another length ball and on middle, Shubman Gill flicks it towards square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill steers it to covers for one.
Another fuller one, KL Rahul taps it to mid off for one.
Slightly shorter one, Shubman Gill punches it to covers for one.
Hint of turn around off, KL Rahul drives it to the point fielder.
Bowls it on off, KL Rahul lunges and defends it away.
Tossed up, on middle. KL Rahul defends it to covers.
On a length and on leg, Shubman Gill eases it to short leg.
On a length and on off, Shubman Gill taps it to covers for one.
Fuller and on off, KL Rahul drives it but finds the fielder at point.
Shorter and down leg, KL Rahul looks to pull it but misses.
Good length and on middle, KL Rahul defends it back towards the bowler.
Bangs a bouncer and on middle, KL Rahul ducks underneath it.
Tosses it up on middle, Shubman Gill defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill eases it to mid on.
Tossed up giving it some air, Shubman Gill moves forward and eases it to mid on.
FOUR! Goes fuller and outside off, Shubman Gill leans and plays a cover drive through covers for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and on leg, Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for one.
A hint of turn and through the middle as KL Rahul blocks it off his front foot.
Bowls a shorter one, around leg. Shubman Gill pulls it but gets a bottom edge as the ball rolls towards square leg, They collect one.
Short of a length angling in, KL Rahul rides the bounce to the mid on region.
Shorter again, KL Rahul awkwardly pulls it but doesn't connect well. Dot.

OUT! TAKEN! The short ball ploy has worked here for Khaled Ahmed. Bowls a shorter length again and down leg, KL Rahul pulls it but doesn't get the power right. The ball carries towards deep backward square leg and Taijul Islam at the fence takes a good catch. Bangladesh finally have a breakthrough in this innings.
Howout: c Taijul Islam b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Goes fuller this time and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to mid off.
Short again, down leg. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill eases it to mid off.
Fuller one on leg with some turn, Shubman Gill moves forward to defend it but gets his pads. A stifled appeal turned down.

Another appeal for lbw turned down. Shakib Al Hasan decides to go upstairs this time. This is fuller and on middle and leg, Shubman Gill looks to defend it but misses and the ball hits his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down and Shakib Al Hasan takes a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat. The ball Tracking rolls and it shows that the ball was missing the leg pole and Shubman Gill is safe yet again!
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Shubman Gill shimmies down the wicket and heaves it through mid-wicket for a boundary! He moves to 48.
Goes fuller and on middle, Shubman Gill covers his line and blocks it away.
Shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara fends it to mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and on leg, Shubman Gill pulls it through square leg for one.
Shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Another shorter one as Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone again.
Back of a length and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick it but misses as the ball hits his thigh and rolls towards silly mid off.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for one. Fifty up for Shubman Gill. His 5th fifty in Tests!
Slightly shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to the man at square leg.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to mid off and scampers through for a single.
FOUR! Finds the gap. Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill reads it well and sweeps it hard and through square leg for a boundary!
Bowls it on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Shorter and on leg, Shubman Gill lets it go.
SIX! All the way. Shorter and on off, Shubman Gill stands tall and pulls it hard and over deep mid-wicket for a maximum!
Shorter and on off again, Shubman Gill pulls it to mid-wicket. The fielder does well and gets a hand on it. They collect one.
Shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara doesn't read it and gets a hit on his shoulder No ball called for overstepping.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to the man at covers.
Shorter and on middle as Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.

Shorter and on off again, Cheteshwar Pujara doesn't read it well and the ball hits his shoulder and falls on the turf. Khaled Ahmed gives a stare to Pujara and Pujara also does not shy away from giving an eye to eye but nothing more than that.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for one.
Tosses it up on middle, Pujara flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Goes fuller this time, Pujara flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fine shot. Touch fuller and on off, Pujara hangs back and drives it through covers for a boundary!
Bowls it on leg as this is defended towards mid-wicket.
Shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and punches it towards deep covers. The fielder does well to stop it. They collect three runs.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back towards the bowler.
Shorter one and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara ducks underneath it.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to the man at mid off.
Goes shorter again and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara reads it well and ducks underneath it.
This one lands wide outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves the harmless delivery.
FOUR! Fine shot. Shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara swivels and pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary!
Tossed up, outside off. Gill taps it to the man at covers.
Bowls it on leg as this is worked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to the man at square leg.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards mid-wicket.
Shorter and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara plays a hook shot towards backward square leg for one.
Bowls it on leg, 77 kph. Gill flicks it towards square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Gill covers his line and defends it away.
FOUR! Perfectly timed. Tossed up giving it some air, Gill waits for the ball and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Slightly shorter one, Gill punches it towards covers for one.

Bowls it on off turning it away, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to block it but misses. A loud appeal from the bowler for a caught behind but the umpire is unmoved. Shakib Al Hasan asks his keeper who says that the ball has brushed the thigh on the way and they do not take the review. The replays confirm that it indeed brushes the thigh on its way to the keeper.
Goes fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it back towards the bowler.
On off again, Cheteshwar Pujara drives it but finds the man at covers.

Another loud shout for lbw turned down. Bangladesh goes for a review this time. Oh, the DRS has gone down for some reason and the onfield decision stands! Unfortunate for Bangladesh. This one was on outside off turning it in, Shubman Gill looked to play at it off the back foot but missed and the ball hits his pads. That was close and Bangladesh players are disappointed. We got only one normal replay which suggested that their was no bat there but unfortunately for Bangladesh, the techinical lapse will not help their cause here.
Fuller one angling it into the batter, Gill defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off, Gill taps it to covers for a single.
Bowls it fuller with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward to play at it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards deep point. They collect two.
FOUR! Easy pickings. Slightly shorter and down leg, Cheteshwar Pujara swivels and pulls it hard through square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, this is defended well.
Bowls it on off with some turn, Gill reads it well and defends it solidly.
This one lands on off, Gill drives it towards covers for one.
Goes on off, this is defended towards mid off.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards silly mid off.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Pujara punches it towards deep covers for one. Fifty partnership up between these batters now!
Goes fuller and on off, Gill sweeps it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Full and at the off stump, 92 kph. Shubman Gill drives it to the off side but finds the fielder.
Fuller one with some turn as Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Gill eases it to mid on. Dot.
Outside off this time, Gill knocks it towards long on for one.
On off, defended solidly.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara drives it but finds the man at covers.
Tossed up, on off. This is defended out solidly.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill drives it but finds the fielder at covers.
Bowls it outside off, Shubman Gill looks to play at it but misses.
Slightly shorter one, 81 kph. Shubman Gill flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara slaps it to point for one.
Fuller and on middle, Shubman Gill taps it back towards Taijul Islam.
Bowls it fuller turning it in, Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to short covers.
FOUR! On the charge. Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara shimmies down the wicket and drills it through long on for a boundary!
Quicker one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.
Bowls it on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it but finds the man at square leg again.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara works it to backward square leg for one.
Tossed up, on off. Shubman Gill knocks it to mid off for one.

Full and skidding into the batter, Shubman Gill looks to defend it off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal but the umpire turns it down. It is probably going down leg and that is why Taijul Islam also seems to be not interested in the DRS.
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill taps it to the man at backward point.

Fuller and outside off, Shubman Gill looks to sweep it but misses. The keeper grabs it and whips the bails off. A loud shout and the umpire decides to go upstairs. Replays shows that Gill was just inside the crease and he is safe!
Bowls it on off, Shubman Gill flicks it towards square leg for one.
Pitched up, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward and defends it well.
Fuller and outside off, 88 kph. Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to third man for a brace.
Tossed up on middle. Gill blocks it off the front foot.
A quicker delivery on middle. Gill works it to mid-wicket this time.
Tossed up, on off. Gill drives it to long off for a single.
Pushed quicker and outside off. Pujara drives it to sweeper cover and takes a single. He looks for the second run but his partner is not interested.
Tossed up on middle. Gill shimmies down the track and knocks it to long on for a single.
Another flighted delivery on middle. Pujara uses his feet this time and works it to long on for another single.
Tossed up, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg and calls for one but Shubman Gill sends him back.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it outside off with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara slaps it to point for one.
Goes fuller again, Shubman Gill covers his line and defends it out.
Another one on off, Shubman Gill defends it out solidly. That will be TEA BREAK for Day 3.
Das starts with a shortish delivery on off. Pujara worls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short in length again and it is outside off. Gill goes back and pulls it wide of long on for a single.
Tossed up nicely on off. Pujara fends it off the front foot.
Tossed up and outside off. Pujara skips down the track and drives it to covers. He looks for a single but is sent back by Gill. Pujara is not happy.
Outside off and turning in. Pujara skips down the track and tries to work it towards the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Tad shorter and on middle. Pujara works it to square leg.
On the shorter side and outside off. Gill punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Pujara blocks it off the front foot.
Short and outside off. Pujara cuts it to deep point for a single.
Goes fuller and on off. Gill fends it off the front foot.
Serves it full and on off again. Gill pushes it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air and on off stump line. Gill gets well forward and blocks it.
Short and outside off. Pujara goes deep in his crease and punches it to sweeper cover for a couple. The lead is now 400!
Tossed up on middle. Pujara skips down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Shimmies down the track and drives this full delivery to long on for a single.
SIX! Gill goes over the top and clears the fence easily! Tossed up on off. Gill dances down the track and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
Shorter in length, on off. Gill punches it to long on for a single.
Shorter and around off. Pujara goes deep in his crease and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
An arm ball on middle. Pujara defends it off the inside half of his blade to backward square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Gill fends it off the front foot.
Shorter in length and around off. Gill punches it to long off and moves into the 90s for the second time in his career.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Pujara blocks it from his crease.
Slower through the air and around off. Pujara with a gentle push towards the off side.
Tossed up on off. Gill skips down the track and plays it back to the bowler.
Again a flighted delivery on middle. Gill shimmies down the track and works it to long on for a single.
An appeal but Pujara was is out of his crease! Tossed up on off. Pujara dances down the track and tries to slog-sweep it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but no damage done.
Shorter in length on off. Pujara works it towards the leg side.
Slower through the air and on off. Pujara calmly fends it towards the leg side.
Gives this delivery some more air, on off. Pujara reaches the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Tossed up on middle. Gill defends it off the front foot nicely.
Slower through the air, on off. Gill with a defensive shot again.
Touch slower and more air on this delivery on middle. Gill blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle. Gill drives it to mid on this time.
Fires it quicker and around off. Gill blocks it again.
Serves it bit full and around off. Gill pushes it to covers and takes a quick single.
Tossed up on off. Gill skips down the track and drives it to long off for a single.
Goes fuller and on off. Pujara works it to fine leg for a single. This is getting very easy for India.
Fuller and on off, Shubman Gill uses his feet again and angles this to square leg. Dot.
Tossed up on middle. Gill skips down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Shortish length and on off. Gill goes deep in his crease and clips it to fine leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on off. Pujara shimmies down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side on middle. Gill works it to deep square leg for a single.
Bowls it quicker and on off. Pujara fends it towards the off side.
An arm ball sliding into middle. Pujara defends it calmly towards the leg side.

Fires a quicker delivery on middle and leg. It goes through with the angle and Pujara who tries to defend it, misses. A big confident appeal but the umpire is not interested and neither is Shakib Al Hasan when the bowler and keeper tries to convince him to to take the DRS.
A flatter one on middle. Pujara blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle. Pujara plays it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Gill skips down the track and blocks it out.
FOUR! Very interesting shot to get to 99 in Test cricket! Tossed up on middle. Gill gets into the position early and reverse-sweeps it through backward point for a boundary.
A flatter and quicker on off. Gill blocks it off the back foot.
Fires it quicker on the pads from 'round the wicket and Gill works it towards the leg side.

FOUR! Shubman Gill gets to his maiden century with a boundary! It was just a matter of time before this man turns his starts into a big score and this might just be the start of a special career. Hasan tosses this up on middle. Gill dances down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and tonks it down the ground powerfully. It goes off the bounce into the fence.
A flatter delivery on middle. Gill blocks it out.
Goes fuller and outside off. Pujara drives it to deep point for a single.
Shorter in length, on middle. Gill goes back and punches it to long on for a single.
Pujara skips down the track and tries to swing it towards the leg side. However, he misses and the ball hits his pads.
On the shorter side and outside off. Pujara cuts it late and takes two as the ball rolls towards the third man region.
Tossed up on off. Pujara paddles it to the fine leg region for a couple.
Fires a quicker delivery, outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
SIX! The intentions are clear now! This is tossed up on off. Gill shimmies down the track and slams it over long on for a maximum.
Touch shorter and on off. Gill steps out and defends it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shubman Gill goes for another one but holes out! Gill makes his intentions clear very early again and Mehidy Hasan cleverly drops it just short. Gill still goes with his lofted shot but miscues it. The ball goes high in the air behind mid-wicket and the substitue fielder Mahmudul Hasan Joy runs forward and takes a good catch. End of a brilliant knock from Gill!
Howout: c sub Mahmudul Hasan Joy b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: A quicker delivery on off. Kohli blocks it off the front foot.
Touch shorter and on middle. Kohli uses his wrists and whips it towards deep mid-wicket and takes a single to get off the mark.

FOUR! India are in hurry now and Pujara gets to his fifty with a boundary! Tossed up on off. Pujara dances down the track and lifts it over mid off for a boundary. Pujara has got his second fifty of this game now.
Quicker and on leg, Virat Kohli flicks it but finds the man at mid on.
Bowls it fuller again as this is defended towards mid off.
Outside off this time, Kohli taps it to deep covers for one.
Another one outside off, Pujara defends it to point.
Fuller again, Cheteshwar Pujara shimmies down the wicket and heaves it over mid on for a boundary!
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it solidly.
Quicker and on middle, Virat Kohli blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Virat Kohli works it to mid-wicket for none.
Another one on middle, Virat Kohli knocks it to mid on for one.
FOUR! Cheeky from Cheteshwar Pujara, Fuller and on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara scoops it over short fine leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it off the front foot.
On leg this time, Pujara tucks it away to the mid-wicket region.
Fuller and on off, Virat Kohli knocks it to mid off for one.
Bowls it on off turning it away, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to reverse sweep but misses and gets hit on his arm on the way. A loud shout but the finger stays down.
Outside off, defended.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward and lofts it over mid off for a boundary!
This one lands on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to covers.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one. Cheteshwar Pujara is showing some aggression here.
Slightly shorter and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it to min on for one.
Another single as this is played towards mid on.
Bowls it on off with some turn, Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it to mid-wicket.
This one lands on leg, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Outside off turning it away, Virat Kohli blocks it to mid off.
Touch shorter and on middle. It keeps very low and kohli just about manages to work it towards mid-wicket. Good signs for Indian bowlers!
Goes fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara moves forward and knocks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Another one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara cuts it towards deep point for a brace.
Bowls it outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to the man at point.
Outside off again, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to short third man for one.
Fuller and on off, Virat Kohli eases it to deep mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara shimmies down the track and heaves it over mid-wicket for a boundary! Pujara is using his feet nicely here.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Virat Kohli knocks it to long on for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and punches it past covers for a boundary!
On off this time, Cheteshwar Pujara looks to loft it but doesn't connect well. Dot.
A single as this is played towards backward point.
This one lands down leg, Virat Kohli flicks it to fine leg for a brace.
Slightly shorter one and on middle, Virat Kohli knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it on off, Virat Kohli eases it to mid on and takes one.
Outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara drills it to mid on for one.
Fuller one and on off, Virat Kohli knocks it to long on for one again.
Tosses it on off, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to the man at point.
Another fuller one as this is played towards mid on for one.
Bowls it outside off, Virat Kohli nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, Virat Kohli knocks it to mid on for one.
Fuller and on off, Virat Kohli eases it to covers for one.
FOUR! Another fuller one, Cheteshwar Pujara gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Tossed up, on leg. Cheteshwar Pujara paddles it towards fine leg for a brace. The ball hits the stumps while the keeper throws it to the bowler and the batters take one more.
On leg as this is flicked towards backward square leg for one.
Full and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it to long on for one.
Fuller one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, Virat Kohli flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara taps it to backward point for none.
Fuller and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara knocks it to long on for one.
Outside off this time, Virat Kohli looks to drill it but doesn't connect well. Dot.
Full, turns in outside the leg stump, and keeps a tad low. Virat Kohli pushes it to mid off for one.
Goes fuller and on off, Virat Kohli flicks it to long on and gets Cheteshwar Pujara on strike with a single.
On off with some turn as Cheteshwar Pujara defends it away.
FOUR! Shorter in length and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara pulls it in the gap through square leg for a boundary! He moves to 95.
Bowls it on off, Cheteshwar Pujara eases it to mid on.
Goes outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Another fuller one, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it towards square leg for one. He keeps his strike for the next over.
Slightly shorter one, Cheteshwar Pujara flicks it to the man at square leg.
Back of a length, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara pulls it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Virat Kohli drives it to covers for one.
Another one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara guides it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Virat Kohli drills it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Virat Kohli defends it away.
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara punches it to the man at covers.
On off, Cheteshwar Pujara lunges and defends it away.
Another one on off, Cheteshwar Pujara defends it out.

FOUR! Finally finds the fence. An amazing knock from Cheteshwar Pujara. Fuller one and on off, Cheteshwar Pujara skips down the track and works it in the gap wide of the diving mid on fielder for a boundary! Century number 19 for Cheteshwar Pujara in Test cricket! His first in 52-Test match innings! With that Cheteshwar Pujara's hundred, India have declared!

Shanto with a solid block off the front foot this time! Siraj got him off the first delivery in the first innings but this time Shanto is upto the task. Siraj lands it on a length, on off. Shanto gets well forward and defends it.
Serves a good-length delivery and it is angled across the left hander. Shanto makes a watchful leave.
On the shorter side and around off. Shanto rides the bounce and punches it through covers for a couple.
A yorker-length delivery on off at 135 kph. Shanto blocks it out.
A fullish delivery, around off. Shanto drives it to covers.
On a length, on off. Shanto is right behind it to block it.
On a length and around off. Hasan defends it towards the point fielder.
Shortish and outside off at 139 kph. Hasan leaves it alone.
Serves it on a good length and outside off again. Hasan makes an easy leave. Umesh need to be closer to the off pole.
On a length and around off at 140 kph. Zakir Hasan blocks it solidly. Much bettter line though from Umesh Yadav.
Serves it on a length, on off at 142 kph. Zakir Hasan blocks it right under his eyes.
Maiden to start from Umesh Yadav! Comes 'round the wicket and lands it on a length, on off. Zakir Hasan blocks it off the middle of his blade.
Serves it on a length, on off. Shanto with a solid defence off the front foot.
Back of a length on off at 140 kph. Shanto looking much more assured here as he blocks it out off the back foot.
Serves it on a length, on off. Shanto fends it from his crease.
Goes a bit fuller on off at 133 kph. Shanto defends it towards the off side.
Siraj comes 'round the wicket and lands it on a length, on off. Shanto is solid in his block again.

FOUR! Bit of a misfield and it allows a boundary! Siraj bangs it short, on off. Shanto pulls it towards mid-wicket and the fielder there fails to get down in time and the ball runs away towards the fence for a boundary.
Lovely tossed up delivery on off. Hasan defends it towards point off the front foot.
Fires it quicker and around leg. Hasan tries to sweep it but misses.
Shortish and outside off. Zakir Hasan cuts it straight to the point fielder.

FOUR! It's gone through again! This time it is Siraj! Tossed up on middle. Hasan sweeps it to backward square leg and Siraj there fails to get down in time as the ball goes through him for a boundary. Ashwin is not happy.
Pushes it quicker and on leg. Hasan tries to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Tossed up on middle. Zakir Hasan defends it out off the front foot.
Lands it on a length, on off. Shanto with a solid defence from his crease.
Almost goes through this one! Back of a length on off at 139 kph. Shanto hops and tries to defend it but the ball bounces low and he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Serves it on a length and around off. Shanto with a block from his crease.
On a length and on off. Shanto pushes it towards the off side this time.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Shanto! Siraj comes 'round the wicket and angles it on the pads. Shanto just helps it on its way as he tucks it to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Bowls a short delivery angling into middle. Shanto pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes it to mid off for one.
Outside off turning it away, Zakir Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, Zakir Hasan bends low and sways a cut past the point region for a boundary!
Outside off, left alone by Zakir Hasan.

This is tossed up on off. Hasan presses forward to defend it but gets an inside edge towards short leg. it goes very quickly to Gill and hits him on the knee and the ball loops up right of him. Gill tries to take it in the second go but fails to reach it.
On off, defended out.
Quicker and on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to the man at square leg.
Outside off as this is blocked off the front foot.
Another one outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto plays it towards covers.
Bowls it on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands down leg, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it towards fine leg. Umesh Yadav runs at it and stops it just before the fence. They collect two. Good fielding!
Outside off with some turn, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but misses.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller one on leg, Zakir Hasan digs it to the man at covers.
Outside off with some turn, Zakir Hasan lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on middle, Zakir Hasan eases it to point.
Tossed up, on off. Zakir Hasan blocks it to gully.
Another fuller ball defended back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one as this is played at mid on.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto lunges and defends it away.
Goes fuller and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to gully.
Another one outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it to short covers for a quick single.
On off this time, Zakir Hasan eases it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Zakir Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it to mid on.
Fuller again, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is played back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter one, Najmul Hossain Shanto rocks back and punches it past mid on for a boundary!
Outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
Fuller and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it solidly.
Another one on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto lunges and defends it away.
Full and just outside off. This is defended on the front foot off the inner part of the bat.
Another one on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it solidly.
FOUR! Fuller and on leg, Zakir Hasan knocks it through mid on for a boundary. Great timing!
Hint of turn and on off, Zakir Hasan eases it to mid off for one.
FIVE RUNS! Bowls it on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it to mid on and takes a quick single. The fielder at mid on has a shy but misses as the ball races away towards the fine leg fence.
Outside off turning it away, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
A dot to end with. Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone. That will be STUMPS for Day 3.
Tossed up on leg to start. Shanto tucks it to mid-wicket comfortably for a single. Nice easy way to get underway in the morning.
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan puts a big stride forward and blocks it.
Pitches on middle and it turns away from Hasan. He fends it from his crease.
Touch short and outside off. Hasan cuts it to the point fielder this time.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Good variaton but Hasan is upto the task and blocks it out.
Slower through the air on off. Hasan is solid on defence again.
Angles a fullish delivery on the pads. Shanto flicks it to the square leg fielder.
Back of a length, on off. Shanto blocks it solidly from his crease.
Serves it on a good length and around off. Shanto gets a bit forward and fends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Lands it on a length, on off angling from 'round the wicket again. Shanto defends it right under his eyes.
Goes fuller and on off. Shanto drives it right of mid off where Ashwin runs to his right and dives to stop it. A single taken.
Back of a length, around off. Hasan fends it off the outside half of his blade towards gully. Not much movement for Siraj in this over.
Starts off with a lovely tossed up delivery on off. Shanto blocks it off the front foot.
On off and it turns further away. Shanto lets it go.
That's an arm delivery on middle. Flatter too and Shanto works it towards the leg side.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shanto drives it to mid on for a single.
Nice delivery! Tossed  up and pitches it around off. The ball turns away sharply and Hasan cleverly lets it go.
No run.
On a good length and around off. Shanto just pokes at it tentatively and gets beaten completely. Lovely delivery!
FOUR! Good shot! Goes fuller and on off. Shanto shows the full face of his blade and drives it down the ground for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Siraj drifts on the pads this time and Shanto very nicely flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
On a good length and around off. Shanto tries to defend it but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and falls just short of the wide slip fielder.
On a length, on off. Shanto blocks it solidly from his crease.
Lands it on a length again and around off. Shanto fends it towards the off side nicely and confidently.

Angles a fullish delivery on middle. Hasan tries to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball goes straight through with the angle. The edge goes past the stumps to short fine leg and a single is taken.
Loopy delivery on off. Shanto with a front foot defence.
Tossed up delivery again on off. Shanto fends it towards the off side.
Bowls it quicker and on off. Shanto with a solid block again.
Keeps it on the off stump line with not much air and Shanto gets forward to defend it.
Goes fuller and angles it on the pads. Shanto paddles it to fine leg for a couple.
Back of a length angling into leg. Hasan pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Once again a short delivery. Sits up at a good height for the batter and Shanto pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Serves another short delivery on off. This time Hasan ducks under it.
Angles a length delivery on the pads from 'round the wicket and Hasan clips it nicely to fine leg for a single.
Things are looking pretty easy for the batters here. Another short delivery angling into leg and Shanto pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Hasan gets nicely behind that and blocks it out.
Tossed up on off. Shanto defends it off the front foot towards the leg side.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Shanto punches it to covers.
Tossed up on off. Shanto with a front foot defence.
Fires a quicker one on middle. Shanto defends it off the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on off. Hasan drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Well played! Ashwin goes for a flatter delivery and pushes it quicker too on off. Shanto though is solid in defence.
A fullish delivery and outside off from 'round the wicket and Zakir Hasan leaves it.
FOUR! Short and punished! Touch on the shorter side and around off. Hasan chops it through the point region for a boundary.
Goes fuller and on middle. Hasan fends it towards mid on and takes a single.
On a good length and outside off. Shanto waits for it and then leaves it alone.
