On a length and angling into off. Shanto with a solid defence off the front foot.
On a good length and outside off at 137 kph. Shanto leaves it alone.
Shortish and outside off. Hasan tries to cut it but misses.
Quicker and outside off. Hasan chops it to the point fielder.
Outside off and it turns away, outside off. Hasan leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off. Hasan drives it to the cover fielder.
Pitches it on middle and it grips a bit off the surface but Hasan goes back and blocks it.
Goes fuller and pitches it just outside off. Hasan leaves it alone. Good bounce there too for Ashwin.
On a length, on off. Shanto blocks it solidly from his crease.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Shanto tries to drive it but it goes off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
On a good length and outside off. Shanto leaves it alone watchfully.
Just short of diving length, around off. Shanto drives it bit uppishly towards mid off.
Goes fuller and around off. Shanto drives it firmly to the mid off fielder.
Maiden over! On a good length, on off at 135 kph and Shanto fends it towards the short cover fielder.
Bowls it flatter on off at 91 kph. Hasan blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle. Hasan pushes it towards the short cover fielder.
FOUR! Nicely driven! Overpitched delivery on off. Hasan drives and drives it quite well in the gap through covers for a boundary.
Tossed up again and around off. Hasan drives it to the cover-point fielder.
Touch short of full length and it pitches around off. Hasan presses forward to defend but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of his blade.
A bit of quicker delivery on off. Hasan blocks it out off the front foot.
On a good length and outside off. Shanto leaves it alone.
Back of a length and angling into off from 'round the wicket. Shanto with a solid block from his crease.
FOUR! Boundaries are coming quite easily for Bangladesh now! Yadav bangs it short and on middle. Shanto pulls and pulls it nicely through backward square leg for a boundary.
On a good length and around off. Shanto leaves it alone.
Back of a length and outside off at 136 kph. Shanto makes a good leave again.
That's better! Serves it on a good length and around off from 'round the wicket. Shanto tries to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten as the ball just straightens after pitching.
On the shorter side and around off. Hasan punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up on off. Shanto drives it to long off for a single.
Slower through the air and around off. Hasan defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Goes fuller and around off. Hasan drives it to sweeper cover for a single.
Goes a bit quicker and fuller on off. Shanto drives it to mid off.
Keeps it out again! Slower through the air and gives it a good flight as well but Shanto is well forward to block it.
Shortish length and outside off. Hasan chops it to deep point for a single.
Serves it on a length and angles it on middle. Shanto blocks it out solidly.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Shanto again with a watchful leave.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Shanto works it to square leg.
Pulls his length back and bowls it outside off at 137 kph. Shanto is happy to just let it go.
On a good length, on off from 'round the wicket and Shanto defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed up on leg as Ashwin goes over the wicket and Hasan works it towards the leg side.
This is a fuller delivery on off. Hasan fends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a single.
Now the batter tries to do something different! This is tossed up on middle. Shanto tries to reverse sweep it but misses and gets hit high on his body.
A full delivery on off. Shanto drives it to the mid off now.
Wow! This one is tossed up on leg and it turns away sharply with some good bounce to beat Shanto who tries to defend it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off. Shanto with a front foot defence.
On a length and around off. Hasan blocks it out.
Angles a back-of-a-length delivery on off at 136 kph. Hasan defends it again nicely.
Oh, good bounce for Umesh Yadav! Shortish delivery and outside off. Hasan tries to cut it but gets beaten as the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Tocuh shorter and outside off. Hasan chops it to point for a single this time.
Back of a length and around off. Shanto fends it towards the off side nicely.
Angles a good-length delivery on off. Shanto gets right behind it to block it.
This is bowled around leg from Ashwin. Hasan sweeps and gets some part of his blade as the ball goes to short fine leg.
Tossed up on off. Hasan drives it to covers this time.
Loopy delivery on the pads and Hasan works it to mid on for a single.
Flighted delivery on leg. Shanto sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
On the shorter side and turning. Hasan tries to sweep it but gets hit on his body.
A quicker delivery on middle. Hasan works it towards the leg side.
On a length, on off at 136 kph. Shanto is solid in his defence.
Back of a length and around off. Shanto rides the bounce and punches it to covers.
Angling a length delivery across the left hander, on off. Shanto fends it solidly from his crease.
On a length and it is outside off. Shanto leaves it alone as the ball goes across him with the angle.
Touch shorter and outside off. Shanto gets on the top of the bounce and punches it through covers for a couple.
On a length, on off at 136 kph. Shanto fends it back to the bowler. 30 overs gone now and India are yet to find a breakthrough. Bangladesh need 428 runs to win.
Pitches it around leg and Hasan sweeps it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shanto paddles it to short fine leg.

FIFTY for Najmul Hossain Shanto! This has been a good knock from the youngster. Lot of skills and grit shown so far but he needs to keep going here. Tossed up on off. Shanto defends it towards the off side and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on off. Hasan pushes it towards the off side for a single.
Gives this delivery some more air, on middle. Shanto gets well forward and blocks it.
Bowls it quicker and around leg. Shanto sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
On a good length and outside off from 'round the wicket and Shanto leaves it alone.
On a good length and around off. Shanto opens his bat face a bit and guides it to third man for a single.
Goes fuller and on off. Hasan blocks it right under his eyes.
On a good length and around off. Hasan defends it towards the short cover fielder.
Back of a length and around off. Hasan chops it towards the backward point fielder.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Hasan watches it carefully and leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shanto sweeps it to mid-wicket for a single.
Touch shorter and around off. Hasan chops it towards backward point for a single.
Tossed up on off. Shanto tries to defend it but gets an outside edge this time. As the ball grips off the surface. It goes towards point for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Hasan works it to mid on this time.
Loopy delivery again on off. Hasan drives it straight back to the bowler.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off. Hasan gets well forward and defends it.
Back of a length and around off. Shanto guides it to the gully fielder.
On a length and around off. Shanto defends it off the outside half of his blade towards the point fielder.
Serves it on a length, on off at 139 kph. Shanto fends it towards the off side. Siraj trying to play the mind games here, has something to say to Shanto here.
Back of a length, on off. Shanto pushes it towards the off side.
Nicely bowled! On a good length and around off. Angling into the batter and Shanto makes a good leave.
Back of a length, on off. Shanto works it towards the mid on fielder. Quite an animated over!
Tossed up delivery on off. Hasan gets well forward and blocks it off the front foot.
Touch fuller and on off at 80 kph. Hasan drives it to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Poor line and Zakir Hasan takes full advantage of it. Tossed up on leg. Hasan sweeps it fine and the ball races away towards the fence.
On off and quicker. Hasan blocks it out.
Touch shorter and around off. Hasan goes deep in his crease and pushes it to covers.
Shortish and outside off. It turns away from Hasan and he lets it go.
On a length, on off from 'round the wicket. Shanto fends it back to the bowler. This time Shanto replies back to Siraj who goes towards the batter on his follow-through.
On a length and around off. Shanto defends it towards the off side.

FOUR! What a confident shot from Shanto! 100 up for Bangladesh! Siraj bangs it short and on off. Shanto pulls it and pulls it firmly towards the square leg fence for a boundary. This time Siraj has nothing to say.
On a length and around off. Shanto fends it towards the off side.
On a good length and outside off. Shanto leaves it alone watchfully.
Lands a length delivery on middle. Shanto clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Well stopped! Back of a length and around off. Shanto goes back and punches it left of the mid on fielder. Patel runs to his left and dives to make a good stop. Just a single.
This one pitches around off and it turns away. Hasan leans forward and takes his bat out of the way.
Goes fuller and around off. Hasan pushes it off the outside half of his blade towards point.
Nicely delivery. Another googly, around off. It turns away and Hasan leaves it alone nicely.
Short and outside off. Hasan cuts it through point for a couple.
Bowls it touch short and on middle. Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Shanto defends it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air on off. Shanto tries to drive it but gets the inside edge on the pads.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Shanto defends it but gets the inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle Hasan clips and the ball hits the knee of short fine leg. The ball loops up in the air a bit but no damage done.
This one pitches on off and it turns in. Hasan tries to drive it but gets hit on the back leg. Patel appeal but no one else seems interested including the umpire.
Tossed up on off. Hasan with a front foot defence.
Goes fuller and on off. Shanto fends it with soft hands.
Tossed up and outside off and Shanto makes a careful leave.
Loopy delivery and around off. Shanto defends it onto the turf.
Nice flighted delivery on off. Shanto drives it to mid off this time.
Pitches it on off and it turns into the batter. Shanto defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Serves it quicker and flatter, outside off. Shanto drives it to sweeper cover and comes back for the second run. Good running.
FOUR! Nicely played! Bowls it fuller and on off. Hasan uses his feet and flicks it uppishly towards the jumping mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Turning into leg. Hasan leaves it as the ball goes off his pads towards leg gully.

Fifty on debut for Zakir Hasan! He has been very impressive. Solid and quite confident of what he wants to do in the middle. Long way to go for this debutant. Tossed up on middle. Hasan reaches the pitch of the ball and works it to mid on for a single.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Shanto blocks it out.
On the shorter side and on middle. Shanto goes deep in his crease and works it towards the leg side.
Loopy delivery on off. Shanto though is equal to the task and blocks it out. Exactly 400 needed now!
Tossed up on middle. Hasan makes room and drives it to covers.
Shortish delivery and outside off. Hasan chops it to the point fielder.
Turning away from around off. Hasan punches it to covers.
Bowls it quicker and fuller on off. Hasan fends it off the outside half of his blade.
Shorter and outside off. Good turn there and Hasan pulls it to mid on.
FOUR! Zakir Hasan is growing in confidence now! Tossed up on middle. Hasan sweeps and sweeps well through the backward square keg region for a boundary.
Shortish and quicker on off. Shanto blocks it from his crease.

Goes fuller and on middle. Shanto works it to mid-wicket for a single. Pujara there picks the ball and fires a throw towards the batter's end but it ends up hitting Zakir Hasan on his left knee. He looks in some pain here.
This is pitched on off and it turns into the batter. Hasn tries to defend it but gets beaten on the inside edge. There is a big appeal from Patel again but the umpire is not interested.
Tossed up on middle. Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls a flatter and quicker one on off. Shanto is well forward to block it.
Keeps it out! Brilliant session for Bangladesh. Patel tosses it up and around off. Shanto presses forward and defends it. That will be Lunch on Day 4!
Good length angling it in, Hasan defends it solidly to short leg.
Another length ball around off, Hasan stands tall and blocks it to mid-wicket.
Good length angling it in, this one lands just outside off. Hasan makes a tight leave. This was close.
Goes fuller and on off, Hasan guides it to backward point for one.
A length ball on off angling it in, Shanto defends it to mid on.
Bowls it on off, Shanto defends it solidly off the front foot.
Tossed up on leg, Hasan works it to square leg for one.
Goes fuller and on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto eases it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, Najmul Hossain Shanto again defends it to the bowler.
Bowls it on middle, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off this time, this one keeps a tad low. Najmul Hossain Shanto guides it to backward point for one.
Fuller and down leg, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but misses as the ball hits his pads and bounces off the deck.
Goes fuller and on off, Shanto defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off, Shanto drives it but finds the man at covers.
Good length and down leg. Shanto works it to square leg for a brace.
On leg again as this is defended towards mid on.
Good length with some extra bounce, Shanto looks to pull it but misses.
Outside off and fuller in length, Shanto defends it to covers.
Fuller and on middle as this is defended towards mid on.
Another dot ball defended towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards mid off.
Outside off this time, Hasan eases it to covers.
Slightly shorter one, Hasan punches it but finds the man at covers.
Fuller and down leg, Hasan flicks it straight to the man at backward square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Finally, a breakthrough has come and there is a smile on KL Rahul's face. On a length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes at it away from his body. However, the ball straightens after pitching and catches the thick outside edge as the ball carries towards Virat Kohli at first slip. Kohli fumbles and almost makes a mess of it as the ball deflects off his hands towards Pant. The Indian wicketkeeper though is aware and first tries to catch it with his left hand but it pops out. However, he keeps his eye on the ball and takes a good catch with both his hands falling forward. The umpires have a chat and after consulting upstairs, it is given out. Najmul Hossain Shanto has to walk back after an amazing knock. Can India build on this breakthrough now?
Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Umesh Yadav

Commentary: Good length and on off, Yasir Ali flicks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan defends it to silly mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
Goes fuller this time, Hasan guides it to point for one.
On a length angling it into the batter, Yasir Ali defends it solidly towards mid on.
Slightly shorter and on off, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off as this is defended back towards the bowler again.
Shorter and on off, Hasan fends it to covers.
Bowls it just outside off with some turn, Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and down leg, Hasan flicks it straight to the man at square leg.
Another fuller one as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Outside off as this is left alone towards the keeper.
Goes fuller and on off, Ali eases it to mid on.
Fuller and outside off, Ali guides it straight to the man at point.
Fuller and on leg, Ali flicks it but finds the fielder at square leg.

Good length angling it in, this one lands down leg. Ali looks to defend it but gets an inside edge on his pads. A stifled appeal for the LBW as the bat is close to the pad but the umpire is not interested as Umesh Yadav too also does not look confident.
FOUR! Fuller and just outside off, Ali looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away the third man fence. Lucky boundary!
Bowls it outside leg, Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Hasan shimmies down the track for a big heave but mistimes it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Ali defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter one as this is punched towards the man at covers.
Angles a quicker delivery on middle. Ali fends it towards the leg side.

OUT! TIMBER! One brings two for India and this has been a good start for India after Lunch. Angles it on middle but it turns away at the last moment. Yasir Ali looks to defend it but misses it completely as the ball rattles the off pole. Bangladesh lose their second one and they need to get their house in order quickly now otherwise things can drift away from them very quickly as India have found some momentum and confidence here. Axar Patel has looked most dangerous among the spinners in this innings and this wicket will increase his confidence more now.
Howout: b Axar Patel

Commentary: Shorter and on off, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan drives it but finds the man at covers.
Good length with some extra bounce, down leg. Zakir Hasan looks to flick it but misses and hits his pads.
Fuller and on off, this is driven towards the man at point.
Fuller and it nips in a long way from outside off, Zakir Hasan makes a tight leave as the ball just airs past the stumps. This was close!
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan guides it to third man for one.
On off, this is defended towards covers.
On off, defended out solidly.
FOUR! Smashed away. A loosener and on off, Zakir Hasan pulls it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary!
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan plays it with soft hands towards mid off.
This one lands outside off, Zakir Hasan eases it to the man at covers. A dot to end with.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Das defends it solidly.
Fuller again, and on off. Das defends it towards mid on.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards the mid on fielder.
Good length and just outside off, Das defends it towards the man at covers.

Outside off and shapes it away, Das looks to defend it but misses. Close! Oh, hang on! There was an edge as replays roll in and the UlraEdge shows spike as the ball is close to the bat. However, none of the Indian players appealed there.
Fuller and on off, Das knocks it straight as the ball deflects off Yadav and rolls towards covers. The batters collect one run.
Bowls it on off, this is defended towards silly mid off.
Fuller again as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Das guides it to deep covers for a brace.
Bowls it outside leg, Das leaves it alone.
Fuller and outside off as this is defended towards covers.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the man at mid on.
A yorker and outside off, Hasan puts his bat as it rolls towards the slips.
Fuller and outside off, Hasan steers it towards covers for one.
Good length angling it in, Das blocks it to the man at mid off.
A yorker right into the blockhole as Das digs it to the man at mid-wicket.
Bowls it on off this time, Das defends it to covers.
Good length and down leg, Das looks to flick it but gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Flatter one down leg, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on off as Hasan defends it to mid off.
Outside off this time, Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off as this is defended towards silly mid off.
Goes fuller again, on off. Das lunges and defends it away.
Fuller and on middle, Das covers his line and defends it out solidly.
Good length angling it into the batter, Hasan flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on the stumps, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside the off stumps, Hasan reads it well and leaves it alone.
Fuller one on off, Hasan flicks it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
Touch fuller and on off, Hasan defends it solidly.
Bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Hasan flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Das guides it to the man at covers.
Bowls it on middle and leg, this one keeps a tad low. Das defends it to short leg.
On middle as this is again defended towards the fielder at short leg.
Outside off this time, Das defends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it just outside off with some extra bounce, Das looks to defend it but misses it completely. Close!
A maiden from Patel. Fuller and on off, Das flicks it to the fielder at square leg.
Fuller and outside off shaping it away, Hasan leaves the harmless delivery.
Good length angling it in, Hasan defends it solidly towards mid off.
Fuller and outside the off stumps, Hasan plays it with soft hands towards the man at covers.
Shorter one and on off, Hasan leans back and lets it go.
Touch fuller and on off, Hasan defends it solidly towards covers.
On a length and on off, Hasan defends it towards the fielder at mid off. Another maiden over.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards mid on.
Another fuller one, Das lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it on off, Das defends it to short covers.
Fuller and on off, Das defends it towards Kohli at silly point.
Bowls it on off, Das defends it solidly off the front foot.
Another dot ball as this is defended towards the man at covers.
FOUR! Siraj bowls it fuller and outside off, this one keeps a tad low. Hasan reads it well and guides it through backward point for a boundary!
Bowls it outside off shaping it away, Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and outside off, Hasan steers it to deep covers for a brace.
Goes fuller and on off, Hasan digs it to covers.
Fuller again and on leg, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Das flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller one with a hint of turn, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg. Dot.
On off, defended out.
Fuller and on off, Hasan flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Hasan steers it towards the man at covers.
Outside off this time, Hasan shimmies down the track to play at it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards mid-wicket for none.
Fuller again and on off, Hasan flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket again.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan defends it to mid off.
Another fuller one, Das defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and outside off, Das uses the pace of the ball and guides it through backward point for a boundary!
Slower one on leg, Das reads it well and flicks it to square leg for one.
Good length angling it in, Hasan covers his line and defends it out solidly.

JUST SHORT OF KOHLI AT SLIP! On a length and outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes aerially and falls just short of Virat Kohli at first slip who takes it on the bounce. This was close!
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
FOUR! Bowls it fuller and on off, Litton Das reads it perfectly and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, Litton Das eases it to point for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery as this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Hasan flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Nicely played. Fuller and on off, Hasan lofts it over mid off for a one bounce boundary.
Another one outside off, Hasan steers it to deep covers for one.
Fuller and on leg, Litton Das sweeps it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Zakir Hasan drives it to covers for one.

Tossed up with some turn, Litton Das looks to defend it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal but the finger stays down. KL Rahul decides to review at the very last moment. Fair delivery and the Ball Tracking shows that the impact is umpire's call. So, the original decision stays and Das will continue.
Beaten! This time the ball goes the other way. Stock delivery, pitches on off and turns away from Das as he gets beaten off the outside edge as he tries to defend it.
Fuller one and on off, Zakir Hasan defends it to mid off.
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan steers it to deep covers for one. He moves to 81.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Litton Das eases it to the fielder at mid off.
Another dot ball as Litton Das again defends this towards mid on.
Bowls it outside leg, Litton Das leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller one on middle, Litton Das flicks it to square leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Litton Das looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads and rolls towards mid-wicket. Dot.
Another one turning it in from outside off, Litton Das looks to defend it but hits his pads again. Kuldeep Yadav is getting closer.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das covers his line and blocks it away.
Sharp turn and down leg, Litton Das leaves it alone.
Touch shorter and turning in around off. Das goes back to cut it but is cramped for room and just manages to get his bat down in time.
Fuller and on off, Litton Das nudges it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle turning it outside leg, Litton Das looks to block it but gets a rap on his pads. Close.
Fuller again, Litton Das knocks it to mid on for one.
Bowls it outside leg, Zakir Hasan looks to plat at it but gets his pads as the ball lobs towards point. Dot.
On off this time, Zakir Hasan pushes it to mid off for one.
Goes fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan flicks it but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, Zakir Hasan defends it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on leg, Litton Das looks for a big heave but gets an outside edge towards third man for a brace. Luckily it didn't carry elsewhere!
Bowls it on off, Litton Das defends it soidly.
Bowls it on leg turning it away, Litton Das looks to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The players decide not to go for a review.

OUT! CAUGHT! Litton Das holes out in the deep! This was on the cards, Das was looking all at sea agianst some crafty bowling from Kuldeep Yadav and now finally departs while trying to break the shackles. This one is tossed up on off. It is probably another googly and Das plays a poor shot which shows that the pressure of some quality bowling got to him. He tries to go over long on but gets no timing on this one and ends up hitting it straight to long on where Umesh Yadav takes an easy catch. Bangladesh are in a spot of bother now and they would have hoped for a better shot from an experienced player like Litton Das.
Howout: c Umesh Yadav b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Mushfiqur Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Bowls it on off again, Mushfiqur Rahim lunges and defends it away.
Bowls it outside off, Zakir Hasan looks to cut it but misses.
Fuller and down leg, Zakir Hasan defends it to mid on.
Fuller again and on off, Zakir Hasan moves forward and works it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim guides it to third man for a brace.
This one lands outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Mushfiqur Rahim moves forward and defends it away.
Tossed up, outside off. Zakir Hasan knocks it to the man at mid off.
Another one outside off, Zakir Hasan cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
Outside off turning it away, Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
Another one on off turning it away, Zakir Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Outside off turning it away, Zakir Hasan lets it go.
Fuller and on off, Zakir Hasan taps it to covers and calls for one but Mushfiqur Rahim sends him back. That will be TEA BREAK for Day 4.
A half an appeal on the first delivery! Short and outside off. Rahim tries to cut it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pitches on off and it turns into Rahim with good bounce. Rahim goes deep in his crease and dabs it behind square on the off side.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tosses it up on off. Rahim reaches the pitch of the ball and works it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fires it quicker on middle. Rahim blocks it out.
Goes fuller and quicker on middle. Rahim defends it off the front foot.
Very full and flighted delivery on middle. Rahim fends it towards short leg.
Tossed up, outside off. Zakir Hasan leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off. Hasan drives it to the cover fielder.
Shortish and outside off. Hasan chops it towards the backward point fielder.
What a lovely bowling! Tossed up nicely, around off. Hasan presses foward to defend but the ball turns away sharply and beats him.
Shortish and outside off. Hasan lets it go as Kuldeep again gets good turn.
Short and outside off. Hasan cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
A full toss on middle. Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
Drifts down the leg side and Hasan tries to sweep it but misses.

Ashwin bowls it on leg again and Hasan gets a glove on it this time as he sweeps it. The ball goes towards the fine leg fence and Rahul chases it and stops it just inside the fence with a slide. Two taken.
A flatter delivery on middle. Hasan blocks it out.
Bowls it slower through the air and on middle. Hasan fends it towards the leg side.
Another flighted delivery on middle. Hasan is solid in his block again.
Touch shorter and on middle. Rahim goes deep and works it to backward square leg.
Pitches it on middle and it turns down the leg side. Rahim tries to clip it but misses.
FOUR! Rahim is looking to be positive here. Tossed up on off. Rahim slog-sweeps it through mid-wicket and though Umesh tries to stop it inside the ropes, he fails to do so.
On middle and turning in again. Rahim works it towards short leg.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle. Rahim plays it with the turn again towards the leg side.
Touch shorter and on leg. Rahim works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Rahim knocks it to mid on and takes a single.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Hasan fends it off the front foot.
Fires it on leg and Hasan sweeps it to short fine leg.
Nice driving length, on off. Hasan drives it to covers this time.
Lovely delivery! Pitches it around off. Just short of full length and Hasan goes for a drive again but this time gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tries a quicker one now. On middle and flatter. Hasan works it towards the leg side.
Shortish length and around off. Rahim goes back and punches it to deep cover for a couple. However, they get an extra run off an overthrow as well as the throw from the deep is a bit wayward.
SIX! What a shot! This man looks some player! This one is tossed up on off. Hasan gets under it and plays a delightful lofted off drive for a maximum over long off.
Slower through the air on off. Hasan defends it solidly from his crease.
Good delivery, pitches on off and it turns into Hasan now. He gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend it.
Shortish and outside off. Hasan cuts it to deep point and Umesh Yadav in the deep runs to his right and stops it just inside the ropes. Two taken.

A fullish delivery and around off. Hasan dabs it towards point and takes a single. Mushfiqur Rahim puts in a big dive to make his ground and seems to have hurt his left knee here. The physio is out and Rahim is looking good to resume now after some treatment.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Zakir Hasan defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Century on debut for Zakir Hasan! What a moment for the young man. The crowd and his teammates are on the their feet and Zakir Hasan raises his bat to soak in the applause. What an assured knock this has been, right from the defensive shot to the aggressive one. Coming to the ball - It is on middle and Hasan sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
A fullish delivery on middle. Zakir Hasan blocks it out.
Fires a quicker delivery on leg. Hasan works it towards square leg this time.
Angles another full delivery on middle. Hasan clips it to mid-wicket.
Turning into middle and Hasan just works it towards the leg side with the turn.
Tossed up and around off. Rahim drives it to sweeper cover for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, Zakir Hasan departs just after getting to his century. It has been a fantastic knock from the youngster but Ashwin has finally got the better of him and Bangladesh lose their fourth wicket. This one is nicely tossed up on off. Zakir Hasan gets well forward and tries to defend it. However, the ball goes off the inside edge onto his pads and loops up in the air in front of Virat Kohli at first slip. The former Indian skipper dives forward and takes it safely to hand Ashwin his first wicket.
Howout: c Virat Kohli b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary: Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to covers for a single.
A flatter delivery on middle. Rahim blocks it off the front foot.
Goes fuller and quicker on middle. Rahim works it towards the leg side.
Pushes it quicker again on middle. Rahim flicks it to the leg side.
Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker on middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.

A big shout for the LBW but the umpire is not interested. Rahul takes the DRS! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that there is an inside edge there. So, the decision will stay and India have lost the review. Coming to the ball - It is a flatter delivery turning into middle. Shakib Al Hasan tries to clip it but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal but no damage done.
FOUR! Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and heaves it towards the long on fence for a boundary.

SIX! Goes again and this time clears the fence. Interesting approach from Shakib Al Hasan! This one is tossed up on middle again. Shakib Al Hasan dances down the track and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to long on for a single.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan eases it to backward point.
Bowls it on middle, this is defended solidly.
Outside off this time, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to covers.
This one lands down leg, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on leg, Rahim flicks it to square leg for one.
on off, this is defended towards silly point.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards mid-wicket.
On middle as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Another dot ball as this is again defended towards the bowler.
Bowls it on leg, Rahim flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
On middle with some turn, Rahim defends it solidly off the front foot.
Outside off, blocked out.
Tossed up, on off. Shakib knocks it to covers for a brace.
Bowls it on off, Shakib defends it to silly point.
Fuller one on off, Shakib flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Another dot ball as this is defended off the front foot.
Slightly shorter one, Rahim punches it to the man at covers.
Full and down leg, Rahim flicks it to square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Rahim blocks it to point.
Fuller and on off, Rahim eases it to mid off.
This one lands down leg, Rahim blocks it to square leg.
Flatter and on leg, Rahim blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Rahim defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Rahim punches it but finds the man at covers.
Fuller and on middle, Shakib defends it to mid off.
Bowls it outside off, Shakib guides it to covers for one. A slight miscommunication but they did well in the end to take a quick single.
Fuller and on off, Rahim defends it solidly.
Outside off turning it away, Rahim flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Shakib guides it to covers for one
This one lands down leg, Shakib defends it with soft hands towards short leg.
Fuller and on middle with some extra bounce, Rahim blocks it awkwardly towards silly point.
Outside off with some bounce, Rahim looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Rahim defends it solidly.
Another one outside off, Rahim guides it to backward point for one.
Fuller and on off, Shakib comes down the wicket and defends it awkwardly. It goes towards the man at leg slips.
Fuller and on off, Shakib defends it solidly.
Bowls a fuller one on off, Rahim works it to square leg for a brace.

Dropped! On a length and outside off shaping it away, Rahim looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge. Pant dives to his right to take it but just manages to get a glove on it. An opportunity missed for India.
This one lands down leg, Rahim looks to flick it but gets his pads towards square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Bowls it on off, Shakib fli ka it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and outside off, Rahim pushes it to covers for one.
On off, Shakib eases it to mid off.

OUT! TIMBER! That's a beauty from Axar Patel. Axar Patel angles it on middle and Mushfiqur Rahim looks to block it but misses as the ball turns away sharply and beats the outside edge of his blade to rattle the off pole. Mushfiqur Rahim makes his way back into the hut and Bangladesh are now 5 down in a jiffy. Nurul Hasan walks in next.
Howout: b Axar Patel

Commentary: Bowls it on off, Nurul Hasan taps it to deep covers. The fielder chases it well. They collect three runs.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to mid-wicket. Dot.
Bowls it on middle, Shakib Al Hasan moves forward and flicks it to square leg for one.
This one lands outside off, Nurul Hasan leaves it alone.

OUT! STUMPED! Axar Patel is turning it on for India with this new ball! Bowls it on off turning it away, Nurul Hasan looks to driv it but misses completely. Pant is quick to grab it and stumps it immidiately. Umpires go upstairs to check. The replay shows that he was just outside his crease and Nurul Hasan has to walk back. Bangladesh are losing their way here! Now, it suddenly looks a very uphill task, two wickets in the over!
Howout: st Rishabh Pant b Axar Patel

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan taps it to covers. Dot.
On a length angling it in, Shakib reads it well as blocks it to mid-wicket.
Good length and outside leg, Hasan leaves it alone.
Fuller one and on off, Hasan defends it solidly towards covers.
On a length and on leg, Hasan defends it to mid on.
Bowls it outside off, Hasan leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and outside off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it through covers for a couple.
Tossed up delivery on off. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and defends it.
Short and quicker outside off. Shakib Al Hasan lets it go.
On the shorter side on off and quicker. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan uses his feet reaches the pitch of the ball and drives it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller again and angling into middle. Shakib Al Hasan works it to mid-wicket.
Serves it on a good length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length and around off. Hasan punches it to the point fielder.
Goes fuller and on the pads at 139 kph. Hasan flicks it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length and on middle. Mehidy Hasan gets right behind it to block it.
Back of a length and around off. Hasan punches it to cover-point fielder.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Bit of swing into the batter and Hasan manages to push it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
A flatter delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and blocks it out.
Touch shorter and on off. Shakib Al Hasan goes back and punches it to covers.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and blocks it.
Fires it quicker on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and defends it towards silly point.
FOUR! Nicely played! Touch short and around off. Shakib Al Hasan cuts it through the backward point region for a boundary.
Turns it into leg. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it but the ball just falls short of the leg slip fielder.
Pitches on middle and it turns in sharply. Hasan tries to clip it but misses and the ball brushes his pads on the way to the keeper. Pant fails to catch it.
Tossed up on middle. Hasan blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Looks like Bangladeshi playesr have decided that they would try to be aggressive here. Tossed up on off. Hasan skips down the track and pumps it over mid off for a boundary.
Shortish and turning into off. Hasan chops it towards the off side as he is cramped for room.
Fires a quicker one on middle. Hasan blocks it out.

FOUR! Finds the edge but it runs away for a boundary! Tossed up on off. It is a googly and turns away to catch an outside edge along the way as Mehidy Hasan tries to defend it. The ball goes between the keeper and the slip fielder for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
Turning into leg and Shakib Al Hasan gets hit on the pads as he tries to leave it.
Turning into leg and quicker. Shakib Al Hasan clips it and does so aerially and just wide and short of the leg slip fielder.
Tossed up on off. It turns away and Shakib Al Hasan just about manages to block it.
Flatter and on off, Shakib Al Hasan looks eases it to the man at mid-wicket.
FOUR BYES! This one lands outside leg, Shakib Al Hasan looks to flick it but misses. Rishabh Pant fails to grab it a well as the ball races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
Tossed up on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it off the front foot.
Another tossed up delivery on middle. Mehidy Hasan fends it off the front foot.
On the shorter side and Mehidy goes back to block it.
Pitches it bit fuller and around off. Mehidy goes deep in his crease again and defends it.
A googly that pitches on middle. Mehidy Hasan fends it with soft hands this time.
Shortish and outside off. Mehidy Hasan makes room and chops it to the point fielder.
Bowls it on off, Shakib shimmies down the wicket and knocks it towards long on. He restricts for a single.
On off, blocked out.
Another fuller one and on off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
This one lands on off, Shakib Al Hasan eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan lunges and blocks it away.
Slightly shorter and outside off, slower too. Shakib Al Hasan cuts it towards backward point for a brace.
Bowls it on leg, Hasan flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Shakib blocks it to silly point.
Fuller one again, Shakib defends it to covers.
slightly shorter and just outside off, Shakib looks to block it but misses.
Another one outside off, Shakib pushes it to the man at mid off.
FOUR! Fuller and on off, Shakib shimmies down the wicket and lofts it over extra covers for a boundary! Excellent placement.
Bowls it on off, Hasan defends it solidly off the front foot.
This one lands down leg, Hasan blocks it to short leg.
Fuller and outside off, Hasan looks to play at it but misses.
Another one with a sharp turn! It pitches around and and turns away. Hasan presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and on off, Hasan steers it to the man at point.
Bowls it just outside off, Hasan looks to defend it but misses. Close!
SIX! Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan reads it well and sweeps it over deep square leg for a maximum! This has been a good counter-attacking knock from the Bangladeshi skipper.
Fuller again, on off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to mid off for one.
Bowls it down middle, Shakib Al Hasan lunges and blocks it away.
Tossed up, on off. Mehidy Hasan eases it to the man at mid off.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Mehidy Hasan punches it but finds the fielder at covers.
Tossed up, turning it on leg. Mehidy Hasan flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
On off, defended towards covers.
Fuller and on leg, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to short leg.
Bowls it on off, Shakib Al Hasan lunges and defends it to mid off.
This one lands on leg, Shakib Al Hasan defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on off, Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to mid off and calls for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses. A direct hit would have been close!
Tossed up and on off, Mehidy Hasan blocks it to silly point.
Fuller and on off, Shakib Al Hasan taps it to the man at covers.
On middle this time, Shakib Al Hasan eases it to mid on.
Bowls it on middle, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
Another one on middle, Shakib Al Hasan lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes fuller and down leg, Shakib Al Hasan blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Shakib Al Hasan guides it to backward point. The fielder is quick and restricts them from taking a single.
Outside off, Mehidy Hasan taps it to the man at mid off.
Toses it up on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it to silly point.
Another one on off, Mehidy Hasan covers his line and defends it solidly.
Fuller and on off again, Mehidy Hasan eases it to the fielder at silly point.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Mehidy Hasan lunges and defends it solidly.
Similar to the last delivery, Mehidy Hasan defends this back towards the bowler. That will be STUMPS on Day 4.
Siraj starts off with a length delivery on off. Shakib Al Hasan defends it towards cover-point.
Serves it fuller and on off at 132 kph. Shakib Al Hasan drives it straight to mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on the pads at 133 kph. Shakib Al Hasan flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Angles a length delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it easily from his crease.
Goes fuller and drifts down the leg side. Mehidy Hasan tries to flick it but misses.
FOUR! lovely shot! Overpitched and outside off. Mehidy Hasan drives it through covers for a beautiful boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan skips down the track and knocks it down to long on. The single is not taken!
Bowls a very full delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to long on and he does not take the single again.
A flatter delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan clips it to mid-wicket this time.
On the shorter side and around leg. Shakib Al Hasan tries to slog-sweeps it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
SIX! This time he connects and this has gone all the way for a maximum! A fuller delivery on middle and leg. Shakib Al Hasan gets low and slog-sweeps it over deep square leg for a maximum.
Serves it fuller and on off. Mehidy Hasan drives it to mid off this time.
On a length and angles it on off. Mehidy Hasan tries to drive it but hits it off the inside half of his blade towards mid-wicket.
A fullish delivery on off. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out solidly.
Lands it on a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it right under his eyes.

OUT! CAUGHT! He is gone and India strike early on Day 5! This is a fullish delivery and outside off. Mehidy Hasan drives away from his body and does not try to keep it on the ground. He just goes through with his shot and hits it uppishly towards point. It goes straight into the hands of Umesh Yadav at point and now India would be looking to wrap this game up quickly here on Day 5! Mohammed Siraj gets his first wicket.
Howout: c Umesh Yadav b Mohammed Siraj

Commentary: Welcomes him with a short delivery, around leg. Taijul Islam ducks under it.
Goes fuller and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan slog-sweeps it along the ground to deep square leg and a single is not taken.
SIX! Another biggie from the Bangladesh skipper and he gets to his fifty in style! This one is tossed up on off. Shakib Al Hasan dances down the track and tonks it over long on for a biggie.
A flatter delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Goes fuller and on off. Shakib Al Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
Goes fuller and on off. Shakib Al Hasan cleverly skips down the track and pushes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Turning into the batter this time. Taijul Islam tries to defend it but the ball bounces and turn into the batter. He manages to play it just wide of leg slip.
On the shorter side on off. Shakib Al Hasan makes room and tries to cut it but misses.
Siraj keeps it on the shorter side on leg. Shakib Al Hasan makes room again and cuts it to deep point. No run taken.
Back of a length, on middle. Shakib Al Hasan goes leg side of the ball and manages to push it to mid off.
FOUR! Too predictable from Siraj and Shakib Al Hasan gets another boundary! Bangs it short and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan makes room again and slaps it to long on for a boundary.

Nice bouncer this time on leg. Shakib Al Hasan gets a top edge as he tries to pull it but the ball goes aerially and falls short of the fine leg fielder. A single is taken, just one ball to face for Taijul Islam again.
On the shorter side, on middle. Taijul Islam works it to square leg this time.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan works it to mid-wicket as he reaches the pitch of the ball.
Touch shorter and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan reverse-sweeps it to the third man region for a couple.
Fires it quicker on middle. Shakib Al Hasan defends it back to the bowler.
Turning into leg this time. Shakib Al Hasan tucks it uppishly towards square leg for a single.
Angling into the left hander and Taijul Islam clips it behind square on the leg side.
Fires it quicker on off. Taijul Islam blocks it out solidly. Have to say, well played!

SIX! Shakib Al Hasan is not going to back away! Siraj bangs it short and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan goes deep in his crease and inside the line of the ball to pull it all the way over fine leg for a maximum.
FOUR! Another boundary! Shortish length again on off. Shakib Al Hasan stays on the back foot and slaps it down the ground for a boundary.
On the shorter side, on middle. Shakib Al Hasan makes room and pulls it to mid on.

On the shorter side and around off. Shakib Al Hasan backs away and cuts it to point for a single. This is poor from Siraj, he is just keeping it on the shorter length, can go a bit fuller for variation.
On a length, on middle. Taijul Islam fends it from his crease.
On the shorter side, on middle and angling into the body. Taijul Islam rides the bounce and fends it towards the leg side.
Shakib Al Hasan gives the charge again and Patel fires it on middle. Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
Touch shorter and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan clips it to deep square leg.
Turning into middle again. Shakib Al Hasan works it to mid-wicket this time.
Slower through the air on off. It turns in and Shakib Al Hasan blocks it out.
SIX! That's a very good shot! Tossed up on middle. Shakib Al Hasan shimmies down the track and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
Shortish length and around off. Shakib Al Hasan chops it through point and takes a single to retain the strike. Very good batting this.
Flatter and on off, Shakib Al Hasan taps it to the man at covers.
Another one on off, Shakib defends it to covers again.
Fuller and on middle, Shakib lunges and defends it solidly.
FOUR! Fine shot and finds the gap. Fuller and on middle, Shakib gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary!
Slightly shorter and on off, Shakib eases it to the man at covers.

OUT! BOWLED! Kuldeep Yadav, you beauty. He strikes in his first over.  This was actually really slow through the air and Kuldeep Yadav does it for India. Tosses it up on leg, it turns away from the batter. Shakib Al Hasan looks to slog sweep it but misses it completely and the ball rattles the stumps. Kuldeep Yadav gets the big fish. The skipper walks out for 84 and it's an end of a very entertaining knock.
Howout: b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Bowls it on off turning it in, Taijul Islam looks to cut it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, Taijul Islam taps it to short leg.
Another fuller one, on off. Taijul Islam defends it to silly point.
Bowls it outside off, Taijul Islam defends it to point.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Taijul Islam hangs back and guides it to point for a brace.
Bowls it down leg, Taijul Islam defends it towards the leg side. A dot to end the over.
Fuller and on off, Ebadot Hossain defends it to mid on.
Another one on off, Ebadot Hossain defends it to silly point.
Bowls it on off, Ebadot Hossain lunges and blocs it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and down leg, Ebadot Hossain looks to block it but gets his pads as the ball lobs towards the man at short leg.

OUT! TAKEN! Kuldeep Yadav strikes again in his second over as well. A good catch taken by Shreyas Iyer at short leg and Ebadot Hossain departs for a duck. Fuller and on middle, Ebadot Hossain looks to flick it but gets the inside half of his bat and Shreyas Iyer takes a good catch at short leg. Bangladesh are nine down now!
Howout: c Shreyas Iyer b Kuldeep Yadav

Commentary: Tossed up nicely on middle. Khaled Ahmed presses forward to defend but misses it. The ball goes off his pads and towards the leg slip where the fielder takes it. There is a bit of excitement among the Indian players as they appeal but the umpire is not interested and everyone on the field including the batter and the bowler have some smile on their face.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Taijul Islam defends it solidly off the front foot.

OUT! BOWLED! They needed 4 wickets on Day 5 and have wrapped this up pretty quickly. Slightly shorter, and it turns just a bit to beat Taijul Islam who tries to defend it off the back foot. The ball knocks over the off pole and it's all done and dusted. India win by 188 runs.
Howout: b Axar Patel
